use this to identify a list of possible actions (which should be recorded below, in the second part of this form).</p>\n<p>During the SWOT analysis, brainstorm how to:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Use strengths with opportunities to initiate positive changes\n</li>\n<li>Use strengths to reduce the impact of threats\n</li>\n<li>Use opportunities to mobilize resources and minimize weaknesses\n</li>\n<li>UControl damage when weaknesses and threats come together\n</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"rTable\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableHead\"><strong>&nbsp</strong></div>\n<div class=\"rTableHead\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Helpful</span></div>\n<div class=\"rTableHead\"><strong>Harmful</strong></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">Internal</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical \"><b>S</b>trengths:<br>[textarea textarea-188 id:textarea3 cols:50 rows:5]<br/></div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical \"><b>W</b>eaknesses<br>[textarea textarea-189 id:textarea3 cols:50 rows:5]<br/></div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">External</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical \"><b>O</b>pportunities:<br>[textarea textarea-190 id:textarea3 cols:50 rows:5]<br/></div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical \"><b>T</b>hreats:<br>[textarea textarea-191 id:textarea3 cols:50 rows:5]</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p><b>List and evaluate possible actions</b></p>\n<p>Record possible actions your organization might take in the table below. When you are finished, evaluate the actions by selecting <b>three</b> checkboxes in each of the remaining columns.</p>\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\"><b>Possible action</b></div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\"><b>Which actions have the greatest potential for positive change?</b></div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\"><b>Which ones are most important to people with disabilities?</b></div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\"><