tivities over a specified period of time. A budget is important for:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Transparent and accountable financial management\n</li>\n<li>Planning</li>\n<li>Fund raising\n</li>\n<li>Programme implementation and monitoring (e.g. comparing the real costs against the budgeted costs), and\n</li>\n<li>Evaluation</li>\n</ul>\n<p><i>Use the following form to prepare a budget for your programme. Select Save when you are finished.</i></p>\n<p>A programme budget must reflect the costs related to the resources outlined in the <b>Decide what resources are needed</b> action plan above. In budgeting, as in identifying resources, it is important to consider the long-term sustainability of the programme, and to build on existing and locally-available resources wherever possible.</p>\n<p>Programme budgets should be prepared very carefully. If you do not have a large enough budget, you may be unable to carry out some programme activities or to sustain the programme in the long term; however, if you set the budget too high, donors and other potential supporters may be unwilling to fund the programme.</p>\n<p><b>Budget for fiscal year _____________</b></p>\n<p><b>Income</b></p>\n\n<div class=\"rTable\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableHead\"><strong>&nbsp</strong></div>\n<div class=\"rTableHead\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Budgeted</span></div>\n<div class=\"rTableHead\"><strong>Actual</strong></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">Grants or subsidies</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical \">[textarea textarea-188 id:textarea3 cols:50 rows:5]<br/></div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical \">[text text-679 id:text111 class:textbox11]<br/></div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">Donations</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical \">[textarea textarea-188 id:textarea3 cols:50 rows:5]<br/></div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical \">[text text-679 id:text111 cla