orrect.\";s:13:\"invalid_email\";s:38:\"The e-mail address entered is invalid.\";s:11:\"invalid_url\";s:19:\"The URL is invalid.\";s:11:\"invalid_tel\";s:32:\"The telephone number is invalid.\";}'),(555,80,'_additional_settings',''),(556,80,'_locale','en_US'),(565,82,'_form','<div class=\"intro\"> \n<h3>Mobilize and manage resources</h3>\n<p>Implementation involves mobilizing and managing several different types of resources.</p>\n<p><i>Complete the following form to as a first step in creating a plan for doing this in your organization. Select <b>Save</b> when you are finished.</i></p>\n<p><b>1. Financial resources</b></p>\n<p><b>Fundraising:</b> Finance for CBR programmes may be mobilized from many different sources. Where possible, the emphasis should be on community-based funding, as this will contribute to the longer term sustainability of programmes. Identify possible funding sources below:</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><b>Details</b></p>\n<div class=\"rTable\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\n<div class=\"rTableRow style=\"width: 100%;\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">Local government grants or subsidies *</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical \">[textarea textarea-183 id:textarea3 cols:50 rows:5]<br/></div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow style=\"width: 100%;\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">Local business donations and corporate sponsorships </div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical \">[textarea textarea-183 id:textarea3 cols:50 rows:5]<br/></div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow style=\"width: 100%;\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">Civil society organizations (e.g. Rotary Club, Lions Club)</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical \">[textarea textarea-183 id:textarea3 cols:50 rows:5]<br/></div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow style=\"width: 100%;\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">Service fees or user charges (for clients with the necessary means)</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical \">[textarea textarea-183 id:textarea3 cols:50 rows:5]<br/></div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow style=\"width: 100%;\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">Special events (e.g. raffles, social events, competitions)</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical \">[textarea textarea-183 id:textarea3 cols:50 rows:5]<br/></div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow style=\"width: 100%;\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">Income-generating activities</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical \">[textarea textarea-183 id:textarea3 cols:50 rows:5]<br/></div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow style=\"width: 100%;\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">Microfinance or a community-based revolving fund</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical \">[textarea textarea-183 id:textarea3 cols:50 rows:5]<br/></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p>* It is important to work with government officials to ensure that CBR funding is provided for in all budgets.</p>\n<p><b>Financial management:</b> Establishing a transparent system for managing finances is very important. This will ensure that your programme is accountable to stakeholders, including funding bodies, community members and people with disabilities themselves. Financial management is a key role of the programme manager, but others may be involved, particularly when programmes are large and involve large amounts of money.</p>\n<p>Good financial management requires that the following tasks be completed:</p>\n<p>[checkbox checkbox-235 id:checkbox01 class:check1] Implement a mechanism to verify that all expenditures are related to planned activities</p>\n\n\n\n\n[checkbox checkbox-263 id:checkbox111 class:check \"Implement a mechanism to verify that all expenditures are related to planned activities\"]<br>\n[checkbox checkbox-263 id:checkbox111 class:check11 \"Maintain financial records regularly and adequately\"]<br>\n[checkbox checkbox-263 id:checkbox111 class:check12 \"Implement systems for appropriate checks and balances\"]<br>\n[checkbox checkbox-263 id:checkbox111 class:check13 \"Report regularly on the financial status of the programme\"]<br>\n\n<p><b>2. Human resources</b></p>\n<p><b>Recruiting:</b> It is strongly recommended that you follow these guidelines when recruiting CBR managers and personnel:</p>\n\n\n<div class=\"rTable\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\n<div class=\"rTableRow style=\"width: 100%;\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical w-50\">[checkbox checkbox-263 id:checkbox111 class:check13 \"Prepare job descriptions for each position\"]<br>\n</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\"><p><b>Note:</b> The job description for each position should specify:<br>\n<ul>\n<li>The roles and responsibilities, and\n</li>\n<li>The experience required\n</li>\n</ul>\n</p><br>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow style=\"width: 100%;\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-263 id:checkbox111 class:check13 \"Seek to hire staff members from the local community\"]<br>\n</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\"><p><b>Note:</b> Individuals from the local community already possess:<br>\n<ul>\n<li>Good knowledge of the local culture and language\n</li>\n<li>Access to community members</li>\n</ul>\n</p><br>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow style=\"width: 100%;\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-263 id:checkbox111 class:check13 \"Whenever possible, recruit people with disabilities or their family members\"]<br>\n</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\"><p><b>Note:</b> This:<br>The job description for each position should specify:<br>\n<ul>\n<li>Demonstrates a commitment to the principles of CBR\n</li>\n<li>Contributes to the empowerment of people with disabilities and their families\n</li>\n</ul>\n</p><br>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow style=\"width: 100%;\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-263 id:checkbox111 class:check13 \"Consider recruiting volunteers (particularly where resources are limited)\"]<br>\n</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\"><p><b>Note:</b> When considering the use of volunteers, be sure to weigh both the advantages (volunteers usually have good local knowledge and are cost-effective) and disadvantages (they often have limited time, and turnover can be high).</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p><b>Training:</b> CBR programme managers and personnel require a wide range of knowledge and skills to enable them to carry out their roles and responsibilities, so it is important to do the following:</p>\n\n<div class=\"rTable\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\n<div class=\"rTableRow style=\"width: 100%;\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-263 id:checkbox111 class:check13 \"Work to ensure that training standards are in place to ensure a minimum level of competency throughout the CBR community\"]</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">&nbsp</div> \n</div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"rTable\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\n<div class=\"rTableRow style=\"width: 100%;\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-263 id:checkbox111 class:check13 \"Identify training opportunities for <b>all CBR personnel</b> that cover the following topics:\"]</div>\n\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">Existing training programmes:</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n\n\n<div class=\"rTable\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\n<div class=\"rTableRow style=\"width: 100%;\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-263 id:checkbox111 class:check13 \"Work to ensure that training standards are in place to ensure a minimum level of competency throughout the CBR community\"]</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">&nbsp</div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow style=\"width: 100%;\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-263 id:checkbox111 class:check13 \"Identify training opportunities for <b>all CBR personnel</b> that cover the following topics:\"]<br>\n<ul>\n<li>Disability rights</li>\n<li>Community development</li>\n<li>Inclusive practices</li>\n<li>Communication</li>\n<li>Basic rehabilitation skills (e.g. identification, basic screening and assessment, basic therapy activities)</li>\n<li>Group processes (e.g. setting up self-help groups)</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">Existing training programmes:</div>\n<div class=\"rTableRow style=\"width: 100%;\">Programme <br>[text text-697 id:text01 class:text]<br>[text text-697 id:text02 class:text]<br>[text text-697 id:text03 class:text]<br>[text text-697 id:text04 class:text]</div>\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow style=\"width: 100%;\">Contact info<br>[text text-697 id:text01 class:text]<br>[text text-697 id:text02 class:text]<br>[text text-697 id:text03 class:text]<br>[text text-697 id:text04 class:text]</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<br><button type=\"submit\" value=\"Submit\">Save</button>\n      <button type=\"reset\" value=\"Reset\">Print</button>\n</div>'),(566,82,'_mail','a:9:{s:6:\"active\";b:1;s:7:\"subject\";s:25:\"INCLUDE: \"[your-subject]\"\";s:6:\"sender\";s:32:\"INCLUDE: <wordpress@include.xyz>\";s:9:\"recipient\";s:21:\"bomoxuxul@parcel4.net\";s:4:\"body\";s:165:\"From: [your-name] <[your-email]>\nSubject: [your-subject]\n\nMessage Body:\n[your-message]\n\n-- \nThis e-mail was sent from a contact form on INCLUDE: (http://include.xyz)\";s:18:\"additional_headers\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"attachments\";s:0:\"\";s:8:\"use_html\";b:0;s:13:\"exclude_blank\";b:0;}'),(567,82,'_mail_2','a:9:{s:6:\"active\";b:0;s:7:\"subject\";s:25:\"INCLUDE: \"[your-subject]\"\";s:6:\"sender\";s:32:\"INCLUDE: <wordpress@include.xyz>\";s:9:\"recipient\";s:12:\"[your-email]\";s:4:\"body\";s:107:\"Message Body:\n[your-message]\n\n-- \nThis e-mail was sent from a contact form on INCLUDE: (http://include.xyz)\";s:18:\"additional_headers\";s:31:\"Reply-To: bomoxuxul@parcel4.net\";s:11:\"attachments\";s:0:\"\";s:8:\"use_html\";b:0;s:13:\"exclude_blank\";b:0;}'),(568,82,'_messages','a:23:{s:12:\"mail_sent_ok\";s:45:\"Thank you for your message. It has been sent.\";s:12:\"mail_sent_ng\";s:71:\"There was an error trying to