sment is an important skill, so CBR personnel should receive prior training and supervision to ensure competency in this area.</p>\n<p><em>This checklist spells out some of the most important tools CBR workers should use to collect the necessary information. Select <b>Save</b> when you are finished.</em></p>\n<p>A skilled assessment professional must be resourceful, collecting information through a variety of different means, including those listed below.</p>\n<p><b>Personal interviews and observation</b></p>\n<p>To identify a persons rehabilitation needs, it is important to seek answers to the following questions, through observation or direct questioning of the individual, his or her family members and other members of the community who are familiar with the individual.</p>\n<p>1. What activities can this individual do and not do?</p>\n\n\n<div class=\"rTable\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical w-50\"><b>Can do:</b></div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical w-50\"><b>Can\'t do</b></div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical w-50\">[textarea textarea-702 id:textarea class:cf-161-1 rows:3 cols:60]</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical w-50\">[textarea textarea-702 id:textarea class:cf-161-2 rows:3 cols:60]</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>2. What does the individual want to be able to do?</p>\n[textarea textarea-548 id:textarea class:cf-161-3 rows:3 cols:140]\n<p>3. What problems do they experience? How and when did these problems begin?</p>\n\n<div class=\"rTable\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical w-50\"><b>Problem</b></div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical w-50\"><b>When and how did this problem begin?</b></div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical w-50\">[textarea textarea-702 id:textarea class:cf-161-4 rows:2 cols:60]</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical w-50\">[textarea textarea-702 id:textarea class:cf-161-5 rows:2 cols:60]</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical w-50\">[textarea textarea-702 id:textarea class:cf-161-6 rows:2 cols:60]</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical w-50\">[textarea textarea-702 id:textarea class:cf-161-7 rows:2 cols:60]</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical w-50\">[textarea textarea-702 id:textarea class:cf-161-8 rows:2 cols:60]</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical w-50\">[textarea textarea-702 id:textarea class:cf-161-9 rows:2 cols:60]</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>4. What areas are affected (e.g. body, senses, mind, communication, behavior)?</p>\n[textarea textarea-548 id:textarea class:cf-161-10 rows:3 cols:140]\n<p>5. What secondary problems are developing?</p>\n[textarea textarea-548 id:textarea class:cf-161-11 rows:3 cols:140]\n<p>6. What is their home and community situation like?</p>\n[textarea textarea-548 id:textarea class:cf-161-12 rows:3 cols:140]\n<p>7. In what way(s) have they adjusted to their disability?</p>\n[textarea textarea-548 id:textarea class:cf-161-12 rows:3 cols:140]\n\n<p><b>Other sources of information</b></p>\n<p>In addition to observing and conducting discussions with the individual and his or her family members, useful information can also be obtained from the following sources:</p>\n<p>1. Review past medical records, and note significant findings:</p>\n[textarea textarea-548 id:textarea class:cf-161-12 rows:3 cols:140]\n<p>2. Perform a basic physical examination of the individual, and note significant findings:</p>\n[textarea textarea-548 id:textarea class:cf-161-13 rows:3 cols:140]\n<p>3. Conduct discussions with involved health professionals/services, and note significant findings:</p>\n[textarea textarea-548 id:textarea class:cf-161-14 rows:3 cols:140]\n<p><b>Note</b>: It is important to keep a record of the initial assessment and future consultations, so an individuals progress can be monitored over time.</p>\n\n\n\n<br><button type=\"submit\" value=\"Submit\">Save</button>\n      <button type=\"reset\" value=\"Reset\">Print</button>\n</div>'),(1475,161,'_mail','a:9:{s:6:\"active\";b:1;s:7:\"subject\";s:25:\"INCLUDE: \"[your-subject]\"\";s:6:\"sender\";s:32:\"INCLUDE: <wordpress@include.xyz>\";s:9:\"recipient\";s:21:\"bomoxuxul@parcel4.net\";s:4:\"body\";s:165:\"From: [your-name] <[your-email]>\nSubject: [your-subject]\n\nMessage Body:\n[your-message]\n\n-- \nThis e-mail was sent from a contact form on INCLUDE: (http://include.xyz)\";s:18:\"additional_headers\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"attachments\";s:0:\"\";s:8:\"use_html\";b:0;s:13:\"exclude_blank\";b:0;}'),(1476,161,'_mail_2','a:9:{s:6:\"active\";b:0;s:7:\"subject\";s:25:\"INCLUDE: \"[your-subject]\"\";s:6:\"sender\";s:32:\"INCLUDE: <wordpress@include.xyz>\";s:9:\"recipient\";s:12:\"[your-email]\";s:4:\"body\";s:107:\"Message Body:\n[your-message]\n\n-- \nThis e-mail was sent from a contact form on INCLUDE: (http://include.xyz)\";s:18:\"additional_headers\";s:31:\"Reply-To: bomoxuxul@parcel4.net\";s:11:\"attachments\";s:0:\"\";s:8:\"use_html\";b:0;s:13:\"exclude_blank\";b:0;}'),(1477,161,'_messages','a:23:{s:12:\"mail_sent_ok\";s:45:\"Thank you for your message. It has been sent.\";s:12:\"mail_sent_ng\";s:71:\"There was an error trying to send your message. Please try again later.\";s:16:\"validation_error\";s:61:\"One or more fields have an error. Please check and try again.\";s:4:\"spam\";s:71:\"There was an error trying to send your message. Please try again later.\";s:12:\"accept_terms\";s:69:\"You must accept the terms and conditions before sending your message.\";s:16:\"invalid_required\";s:22:\"The field is required.\";s:16:\"invalid_too_long\";s:22:\"The field is too long.\";s:17:\"invalid_too_short\";s:23:\"The field is too short.\";s:12:\"invalid_date\";s:29:\"The date format is incorrect.\";s:14:\"date_too_early\";s:44:\"The date is before the earliest one allowed.\";s:13:\"date_too_lat