inclusive education in the communities and gain their support.</p>\n\n<p><i>Complete the following form to identify the support strategies you believe will work best in your situation. Select Save when you are finished.</i></p>\n\n<p><b>1. Getting Started </b></p>\n<p>Before you get started, you\'ll want to assess the situation in your community. Is there a primary school? If so, what does the school do for students with disabilities? What are family attitudes about disabilities? Ask members of the community about the existing situation and attitudes. As you assess the existing situation and attitudes surrounding disabilities, you may identify some awareness gaps in your community. Use the table below to reflect and identify some possible areas where you can raise awareness.</p>\n\n\n<div class=\"rTable\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableHead p-2\"><strong>Existing situation</strong></div>\n<div class=\"rTableHead p-2\"><strong>Potential awareness gap</strong></div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[textarea textarea-728 id:cf-277-1 class:cf-277-1 cols:50 rows:3]</p></div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[textarea textarea-728 id:cf-277-1 class:cf-277-1 cols:50 rows:3]</p></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p><b>2. Mobilizing activities </b></p>\n<p>After characterizing the existing situation in your community, you can plan some activities to raise awareness about inclusive education and gain support. Some activities may be a better fit for the awareness gaps in your community than others. Use the list below as a starting point to think of more.</p>\n\n<div class=\"rTable\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-699 id:cf-277-2 class:cf-277-2 \"Use radio, public meetings, posters, street theatre, TV, the Internet and special events, such as the International Day of Persons with Disabilities to raise awareness about the importance of inclusion and the right to education for all\"]</div>\n\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\"><p>Identify the forms of media and messages that you might use:</p>\n\n[textarea textarea-728 id:cf-277-1 class:cf-277-1 cols:50 rows:3]\n\n<b>Examples:</b>\n \n<ul>\n<li>Radio message about inclusive education for parents who frequently listen to the local channel.</li>\n<li>Posters explaining benefits of inclusive education to hang around the community centre.</li>\n</ul></div></div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-699 id:cf-277-2 class:cf-277-2 \"Involve disabled people\'s organizations and parents\' associations in leading discussions about the barriers preventing children with disabilities from attending school\"]</div>\n\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\"><p>Identify potential organizations and associations to lead discussions in the community:</p>\n\n[textarea textarea-728 id:cf-277-1 class:cf-277-1 cols:50 rows:3]\n</div></div>\n\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-699 id:cf-277-2 class:cf-277-2 \"Use child-to-child activities in schools to raise awareness among children\"]</div>\n\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\"><p>Brainstorm some possible child-to-child activities:</p>\n[textarea textarea-728 id:cf-277-1 class:cf-277-1 cols:50 rows:3]\n</div></div>\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-699 id:cf-277-2 class:cf-277-2 \"Find out about existing policies and resources that could support efforts towards inclusive primary education\"]</div>\n\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\"><p>Identify the existing policies and resources here:</p>\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[text text-875 id:cf-277-3 class:cf-277-3 cols:5 rows:3]</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[text text-875 id:cf-277-3 class:cf-277-3 cols:5 rows:3]</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[text text-875 id:cf-277-3 class:cf-277-3 cols:5 rows:3]</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[text text-875 id:cf-277-3 class:cf-277-3 cols:5 rows:3]</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[text text-875 id:cf-277-3 class:cf-277-3 cols:5 rows:3]</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[text text-875 id:cf-277-3 class:cf-277-3 cols:5 rows:3]</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<button type=\"submit\" value=\"Submit\">Save</button>\n      <button type=\"reset\" value=\"Reset\">Print</button>'),(2023,277,'_mail','a:9:{s:6:\"active\";b:1;s:7:\"subject\";s:25:\"INCLUDE: \"[your-subject]\"\";s:6:\"sender\";s:32:\"INCLUDE: <wordpress@include.xyz>\";s:9:\"recipient\";s:21:\"bomoxuxul@parcel4.net\";s:4:\"body\";s:165:\"From: [your-name] <[your-email]>\nSubject: [your-subject]\n\nMessage Body:\n[your-message]\n\n-- \nThis e-mail was sent from a contact form on INCLUDE: (http://include.xyz)\";s:18:\"additional_headers\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"attachments\";s:0:\"\";s:8:\"use_html\";b:0;s:13:\"exclude_blank\";b:0;}'),(2024,277,'_mail_2','a:9:{s:6:\"active\";b:0;s:7:\"subject\";s:25:\"INCLUDE: \"[your-subject]\"\";s:6:\"sender\";s:32:\"INCLUDE: <wordpress@include.xyz>\";s:9:\"recipient\";s:12:\"[your-email]\";s:4:\"body\";s:107:\"Message Body:\n[your-message]\n\n-- \nThis e-mail was sent from a contact form on INCLUDE: (http://include.xyz)\";s:18:\"additional_headers\";s:31:\"Reply-To: bomoxuxul@parcel4.net\";s:11:\"attachments\";s:0:\"\";s:8:\"use_html\";b:0;s:13:\"exclude_blank\";b:0;}'),(2025,277,'_messages','a:23:{s:12:\"mail_sent_ok\";s:45:\"Thank you for your message. It has been sent.\";s:12:\"mail_sent_ng\";s:71:\"There was an error trying to send your message. Please try again later.\";s:16:\"validation_error\";s:61:\"One or more fields have an error. Please check and try again.\";s:4:\"spam\";s:71:\"There was an error trying to send your me