re partnering together in education for the childrens sake. Use this list of suggested activities below as a starting point to think of more ideas.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"rTable\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-838 id:cf-321-1 class:cf-321-1 \"Listen and talk to family members about:\"]<ul>\n<li>The child with disabilities\' strengths and challenges</li>\n<li>The support needed by the child and other family members</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">Use this table as a template for talking with the parents of the children with disabilities.\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableHead p-2 vertical\"><strong>Strengths</strong></div>\n<div class=\"rTableHead p-2 vertical\"><strong>Needs (of child)</strong></div>\n<div class=\"rTableHead p-2 vertical\"><strong>Challenges</strong></div>\n<div class=\"rTableHead p-2 vertical\"><strong>Needs (of family)</strong></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[textarea textarea-187 id:textarea1 class:textarea cols:10 rows:1]</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[textarea textarea-187 id:textarea1 class:textarea cols:10 rows:1]</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[textarea textarea-187 id:textarea1 class:textarea cols:10 rows:1]</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[textarea textarea-187 id:textarea1 class:textarea cols:10 rows:1]</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"rTable\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-430 id:cf-244-1 class:cf-244-1 \"Liaise between home and school, helping teachers and family members to listen to one another\"]</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\"><div class=\"rTableRow\">&nbsp</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"rTable\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-430 id:cf-244-1 class:cf-244-1 \"Observe the child with a disability in the home and explore ways in which learning in school can be continued and supported at home\"]</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\"><div class=\"rTableRow\">&nbsp</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n<div class=\"rTable\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-430 id:cf-244-1 class:cf-244-1 \"Help ensure that all decisions are in the best interests of the child, and that his or her rights are protected and realized\"]</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\"><b>Note:</b> Parents may sometimes: \n<ul>\n<li>Be overprotective</li>\n<li>Have a limited belief in their childs capabilities</li>\n<li>Want to prioritize the needs of their other children</li>\n</ul><p>Each of these may require a different approach. First identify what, if any, kinds of beliefs already exist, and work with parents to overcome incorrect assumptions and misguided attitudes\n</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n<div class=\"rTable\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-430 id:cf-244-1 class:cf-244-1 \"Promote inclusion with the support of parents\"]</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\"><b>Note:</b><p> Parents can play a major role  there are many examples where parents have joined together and changed a local schools attitudes and practices so their children are included.</p> \n<p>Identify parents in your community who could serve as champions for inclusion:</p>\n[textarea textarea-581 id:cf-321-1 class:cf-321-1 cols:60 rows:6]</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n<div class=\"rTable\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-430 id:cf-244-1 class:cf-244-1 \"Work with parents of children without disabilities to encourage their support for inclusion\"]</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\"><b>Note:</b> Remember that parents will have different opinions about inclusive education. Some will support the decision to include children with disabilities, while others may feel that their children will be disadvantaged. Work with all parents while being sensitive to these different opinions.</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>Consider this scenario. You have been approached by the parent of a child with no arms who is being refused entry into one of the local primary schools in your community.</p>\n<p>What activities could you take with the family of the child to support them and address this issue?</p>\n[textarea textarea-944 id:cf-321-1 class:cf-321-1 cols:120 rows:6]'),(2349,321,'_mail','a:9:{s:6:\"active\";b:1;s:7:\"subject\";s:25:\"INCLUDE: \"[your-subject]\"\";s:6:\"sender\";s:32:\"INCLUDE: <wordpress@include.xyz>\";s:9:\"recipient\";s:21:\"bomoxuxul@parcel4.net\";s:4:\"body\";s:165:\"From: [your-name] <[your-email]>\nSubject: [your-subject]\n\nMessage Body:\n[your-message]\n\n-- \nThis e-mail was sent from a contact form on INCLUDE: (http://include.xyz)\";s:18:\"additional_headers\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"attachments\";s:0:\"\";s:8:\"use_html\";b:0;s:13:\"exclude_blank\";b:0;}'),(2351,321,'_mail_2','a:9:{s:6:\"active\";b:0;s:7:\"subject\";s:25:\"INCLUDE: \"[your-subject]\"\";s:6:\"sender\";s:32:\"INCLUDE: <wordpress@include.xyz>\";s:9:\"recipient\";s:12:\"[your-email]\";s:4:\"body\";s:107:\"Message Body:\n[your-message]\n\n-- \nThis e-mail was sent from a contact form on INCLUDE: (http://include.xyz)\";s:18:\"additional_headers\";s:31:\"Reply-To: bomoxuxul@parcel4.net\";s:11:\"attachments\";s:0:\"\";s:8:\"use_html\";b:0;s:13:\"exclude_blank\";b:0;}'),(2353,321,'_messages','a:23:{s:12:\"mail_sent_ok\";s:45:\"Thank you for your message. It has been sent.\";s:12:\"mail_sent_ng\";s:71:\"There was an error trying to send your message. Please try again later.\";s:16:\"validation_error\";s:61:\"One or more fields have an error. Please check and try again.\";s:4:\"spam\";s:71:\"There was an error 