ws exist, but are not given the help and budgetary support to implement these. CBR should, wherever possible, lobby for existing facilities to become inclusive rather than for the creation of separate facilities.</p>\n<p><em>Complete the following form to identify the support strategies you believe will work best in your situation. Select Save when you are finished.</em></p>\n<p>Identify some potential partners and allies that your organisation can work with in order to advocate for further inclusion. Who are potential contacts at these organizations? What is their area of focus and interest? Once you have identified these potential partners, make an effort to connect with them and to understand each other\'s goals, work, and interests. Keep in mind that though there may be some differing interests in the programmes and groups you identify, you can find common ground in order to mutually support the inclusion of children with disabilities in early childhood care.</p>\n\n<div class=\"rTable\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableHead p-2 vertical\"><b>Persons or groups</b></div>\n<div class=\"rTableHead p-2 vertical\"><b>Area of focus</b></div>\n<div class=\"rTableHead p-2 vertical\"><b>Contact information</b></div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2\">[text text-15 id:cf-265-1 class:cf-265-1]</div> \n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2\">[text text-15 id:cf-265-1 class:cf-265-1]</div> \n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2\">[text text-15 id:cf-265-1 class:cf-265-1]</div> \n</div>\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2\">[text text-15 id:cf-265-1 class:cf-265-1]</div> \n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2\">[text text-15 id:cf-265-1 class:cf-265-1]</div> \n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2\">[text text-15 id:cf-265-1 class:cf-265-1]</div> \n</div>\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2\">[text text-15 id:cf-265-1 class:cf-265-1]</div> \n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2\">[text text-15 id:cf-265-1 class