 wheelchairs.</p>\n<p><em>Use the planning tool below to think through how you can help to make schools more welcoming and accessible. Select <b>Save</b> when you are finished.</em></p>\n<p><b>1. Assess the situation</b></p>\n<p>Assess the situation in each local school, and identify some possible ways of improving the situation. Use the questions below as a starting point to reflect on the existing situation at school.</p>\n\n<div class=\"rTable\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableHead p-2 vertical\">&nbsp</div>\n<div class=\"rTableHead p-2 vertical\"><strong>Situation</strong></div>\n<div class=\"rTableHead p-2 vertical\"><strong>Solution</strong></div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">How accessible and welcoming is the environment?\n<ul>\n<li>Is it accessible for all children who have mobility impairments?</li>\n<li>Can visually-impaired students move around easily?</li>\n<li>Are play areas inviting and accessible for all children?</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[textarea textarea-592 id:cf-140-1 class:textarea rows:5 cols:35]</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[textarea textarea-592 id:cf-140-2 class:textarea rows:5 cols:35]</div>\n</div>\n\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">Are parents and visitors welcome?</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[textarea textarea-592 id:cf-140-1 class:textarea rows:5 cols:35]</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[textarea textarea-592 id:cf-140-2 class:textarea rows:5 cols:35]</div>\n</div>\n\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">What is the general condition of the buildings and equipment?\n<ul>\n<li>Is the school clean and well cared for?</li>\n<li>Are repairs needed?</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[textarea textarea-592 id:cf-140-1 class:textarea rows:5 cols:35]</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[textarea textarea-592 id:cf-140-2 class:textarea rows:5 cols:35]</div>\n</div>\n\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">What are the sanitation facilities like?\n<ul>\n<li>Are toilets private, clean and accessible to all, including students with disabilities and young women?</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[textarea textarea-592 id:cf-140-1 class:textarea rows:5 cols:35]</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[textarea textarea-592 id:cf-140-2 class:textarea rows:5 cols:35]</div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">Is there clean water available for washing and drinking?</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[textarea textarea-592 id:cf-140-1 class:textarea rows:5 cols:35]</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[textarea textarea-592 id:cf-140-2 class:textarea rows:5 cols:35]</div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">Is there sufficient light in the rooms?</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[textarea textarea-592 id:cf-140-1 class:textarea rows:5 cols:35]</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[textarea textarea-592 id:cf-140-2 class:textarea rows:5 cols:35]</div>\n</div>\n\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">Are there clear notices and signboards around the school?\n<ul>\n<li>Are these adapted so that visually-impaired students can use them?</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[textarea textarea-592 id:cf-140-1 class:textarea rows:5 cols:35]</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[textarea textarea-592 id:cf-140-2 class:textarea rows:5 cols:35]</div>\n</div>\n\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">Are there any other items to note about the school?</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[textarea textarea-592 id:cf-140-1 class:textarea rows:5 cols:35]</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[textarea textarea-592 id:cf-140-2 class:textarea rows:5 cols:35]</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p><b>2. Taking action</b></p>\n<p>Now what are some practical steps that you could take with the local primary school to create an accessible environment? Work with school administrators and other personnel to implement these changes. Remember that a welcoming environment is more than just ramps and other physical supports. For example, a school can be made more welcoming by:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Putting up posters and drawings showing positive images of students with and without disabilities from different backgrounds and ethnicities</li>\n<li>Developing policies promoting tolerance and condemning bullying</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"rTable\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[text text-281 id:cf-331-1 class:cf-331-1]</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[text text-281 id:cf-331-1 class:cf-331-1]</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[text text-281 id:cf-331-1 class:cf-331-1]</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[text text-281 id:cf-331-1 class:cf-331-1]</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[text text-281 id:cf-331-1 class:cf-331-1]</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[text text-281 id:cf-331-1 class:cf-331-1]</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[text text-281 id:cf-331-1 class:cf-331-1]</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[text text-281 id:cf-331-1 class:cf-331-1]</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[text text-281 id:cf-331-1 class:cf-331-1]</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[text text-281 id:cf-331-1 class:cf-331-1]</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n\n<br><button type=\"submit\" value=\"Submit\">Save</button>\n      <button type=\"reset\" value=\"Reset\">Print</button>\n</div>'),(2451,330,'_mail','a:9:{s:6:\"active\";b:1;s:7:\"subject\";s:25:\"INCLUDE: \"[your-subject]\"\";s:6:\"sender\";s:32:\"INCLUDE: <wordpress@include.xyz>\";s:9:\"recipient\";s:21:\"bomoxuxul@parcel4.net\";s:4:\"body\";s:165:\"From: [your-name] <[your-email]>\nSubject: [your-subject]\n\nMessage Body:\n[your-message]\n\n-- \nThis e-mail was sent from a contact form on INCLUDE: (http://include.xyz)\";s:18:\"additional_headers\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"attachments\";s:0:\"\";s:8:\"use_html\";b:0;s:13:\"exclude_blank\";b:0;}'),(2452,330,'_mail_2','a:9:{s:6:\"active\";b:0;s:7:\"subject\";s:25:\"INCLUDE: \"[your-subject]\"\";s:6:\"sender\";s:32:\"INCLUDE: <wordpress@include.xyz>\";s:9:\"recipient\";s:12:\"[your-email]\";s:4:\"body\";s:107:\"Message Body:\n[your-message]\n\n-- \nThis e-mail was sent from a contact form on INCLUDE: (http://include.xyz)\";s:18:\"additional_headers\";s:31:\"Reply-To: bomoxuxul@parcel4.net\";s:11:\"attachments\";s:0:\"\";s:8:\"use_html\";b:0;s:13:\"exclude_blank\";b:0;}'),(2453,330,'_messages','a:23:{s:12:\"mail_sent_ok\";s:45:\"Thank you for your message. It has been sent.\";s:12:\"mail_sent_ng\";s:71:\"There was an error trying to send your message. Please try again later.\";s:16:\"validation_error\";s:61:\"One or more fields have an error. Please check and try again.\";s:4:\"spam\";s:71:\"There was an error trying to send your message. Please try again later.\";s:12:\"accept_terms\";s:69:\"You must accept the terms and conditions before sending your message.\";s:16:\"invalid_required\";s:22:\"The field is required.\";s:16:\"invalid_too_long\";s:22:\"The field is too long.\";s:17:\"invalid_too_short\";s:23:\"The field is too short.\";s:12:\"invalid_date\";s:29:\"The date format is incorrect.\";s:14:\"date_too_early\";s:44:\"The date is before the earliest one allowed.\";s:13:\"date_too_late\";s:41:\"The date is after the latest one allowed.\";s:13:\"upload_failed\";s:46:\"There was an unknown error uploading the file.\";s:24:\"upload_file_type_invalid\";s:49:\"You are not allowed to upload files of this type.\";s:21:\"upload_file_too_large\";s:20:\"The file is too big.\";s:23:\"upload_failed_php_error\";s:38:\"There was an error uploading the file.\";s:14:\"invalid_number\";s:29:\"The number format is invalid.\";s:16:\"number_too_small\";s:47:\"The number is smaller than the minimum allowed.\";s:16:\"number_too_large\";s:46:\"The number is larger than the maximum allowed.\";s:23:\"quiz_answer_not_correct\";s:36:\"The answer to the quiz is incorrect.\";s:17:\"captcha_not_match\";s:31:\"Your entered code is incorrect.\";s:13:\"invalid_email\";s:38:\"The e-mail address entered is invalid.\";s:11:\"invalid_url\";s:19:\"The URL is invalid.\";s:11:\"invalid_tel\";s:32:\"The telephone number is invalid.\";}'),(2454,330,'_additional_settings',''),(2455,330,'_locale','en_US'),(2480,332,'_form','<div class=\"intro\"> \n<h5><b>Help create a learning environment</b></h5>\n<p>\'Learning environment\' refers to all the activities and approaches that need to be in place so that all children have the opportunity and support to achieve their highest potential. There are many ways to help create a learning environment for inclusive primary education. Depending on the existing structures, you may choose to use some of the methods recommended here, or design your own.</p>\n<p><em>Complete the following form to identify the support strategies you believe will work best in your situation. Select Save when you are finished.</em></p>\n<p>There are many ways to create an inclusive learning environment. This planning tool focuses on a six-prong approach. Depending on the existing situation in the community, your organisation may emphasize certain aspects more than others. Use this as a guide to help you determine possible courses of action.</p>\n<p><b>1. Start with the school</b></p>\n<p>Find out about the current situation in the local primary school by organizing a workshop for teachers, school staff, parents, community leaders and students. Examples of questions to discuss are given below.</p>\n\n\n<div class=\"rTable\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableHead p-2 vertical\"><strong>Question</strong></div>\n<div class=\"rTableHead p-2 vertical\"><strong>Notes</strong></div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">What is the attitude of the head teacher, \nclass teachers and other children towards children with disabilities?</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[textarea textarea-592 id:cf-140-1 class:textarea rows:4 cols:45]</div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">Are there children with disabilities already in school?</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[textarea textarea-592 id:cf-140-1 class:textarea rows:4 cols:45]</div>\n</div>\n\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">What percentage of the children in school are girls?</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[textarea textarea-592 id:cf-140-1 class:textarea rows:4 cols:45]</div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">What are the dropout, repeater and completion rates?\n</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[textarea textarea-592 id:cf-140-1 class:textarea rows:4 cols:45]</div>\n</div>\n\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">What is the quality of teaching and learning?</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[textarea textarea-592 id:cf-140-1 class:textarea rows:4 cols:45]</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">Are there any teachers with disabilities?</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[textarea textarea-592 id:cf-140-1 class:textarea rows:4 cols:45]</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">What barriers (in terms of resources, structures, or attitudes) get in the way of inclusive education?</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[textarea textarea-592 id:cf-140-1 class:textarea rows:4 cols:45]</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">Are there any other questions specific to your context that you want to ask at this stage?</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[textarea textarea-592 id:cf-140-1 class:textarea rows:4 cols:45]</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>By focusing on the whole-school system, CBR can help teachers understand what a social model approach to inclusion means in practice.</p>\n<p><b>2. Focus on quality</b></p>\n<p>Working to ensure equal access for children with disabilities is only one part of the inclusion process. What happens inside the classroom, such as quality of education, is extremely important. Poor teaching quality is very common, and often, large numbers of children may not be learning or participating. Working together to help children with disabilities learn often leads to an improved teaching and learning environment for all children.</p>\n<p>CBR programmes should encourage teachers to:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Be creative</li>\n<li>Solve problems together</li>\n<li>Use existing resources flexibly</li>\n<li>Observe what is happening</li>\n<li>Listen to children</li>\n<li>Build on the strengths of the students</li>\n<p>A whole-school approach is more effective than focusing on one particular teacher; and the head teachers support is crucial. Make sure to set time to work directly with the head teacher to gain support and buy-in, and to work with all teachers to brainstorm additional ideas.</p>\n\n<b>3. Provide training and support for teachers</b>\n<p>Often teachers have limited knowledge about children with disabilities. Ongoing training in the school environment is the most effective way to train teachers. CBR can develop and provide training and resources for a variety of topics, including:</p>\n\n<div class=\"rTable\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableHead p-2 vertical\"><strong>Topics</strong></div>\n<div class=\"rTableHead p-2 vertical\"><strong>Write your ideas here, if applicable for your community and context</strong></div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-723 id:cf-77-1 class:cf-77-1 \"Different impairments and their implications for learning\"]</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[textarea textarea-592 id:cf-140-1 class:textarea rows:4 cols:45]</div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-723 id:cf-77-1 class:cf-77-1 \"Different modes, means and forms of communication\"]</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[textarea textarea-592 id:cf-140-1 class:textarea rows:4 cols:45]</div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-723 id:cf-77-1 class:cf-77-1 \"Daily living skills, orientation and mobility skills\"]</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[textarea textarea-592 id:cf-140-1 class:textarea rows:4 cols:45]</div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-723 id:cf-77-1 class:cf-77-1 \"Assistive devices, teaching aids and equipment\"]</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[textarea textarea-592 id:cf-140-1 class:textarea rows:4 cols:45]</div>\n</div>\n\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-723 id:cf-77-1 class:cf-77-1 \"Monitoring and evaluation of inclusive primary education with the active involvement of children\"]</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[textarea textarea-592 id:cf-140-1 class:textarea rows:4 cols:45]</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p><b>4. Encourage change in curricula and teaching methods</b></p>\n<p>CBR can liaise between local primary schools, the community, non-governmental organizations and district education departments to assist teachers in making curricula flexible and teaching methods learner-centred. This will benefit all children.</p>\n<p>Usually local primary schools and CBR will have limited freedom to adapt the curriculum and teaching methods. In many countries, there are strict government controls. But small, simple changes are possible at the local level, and it may also be possible to lobby for change at the district and national levels. Examples of how curricula and teaching methods can become more flexible include:</p>\n\n<div class=\"rTable\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-723 id:cf-77-1 class:cf-77-1 \"Get children to work in small groups\"]</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">&nbsp</div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-723 id:cf-77-1 class:cf-77-1 \"Start a \'buddy\' system  putting children in pairs to support each other\"]</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\"><b>Examples: </b>Pair one child who has difficulty in learning with another child who learns more easily\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-723 id:cf-77-1 class:cf-77-1 \"Team teaching\"]</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\"><b>Note: </b>This can free up one adult to move around the class to help those who are having more difficulty.\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-723 id:cf-77-1 class:cf-77-1 \"Create learning aids and equipment out of local materials. This can help students with learning difficulties\"]</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\"><b>Examples: </b>\n<ul>\n<li>Sticks</li>\n<li>Stones</li>\n<li>Bottle tops</li>\n<li>Seeds</li>\n</ul></div>\n</div>\n\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-723 id:cf-77-1 class:cf-77-1 \"Seek the active participation of students, particularly children with disabilities, girls and those who seem to be less involved\"]</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">&nbsp</div>\n</div>\n\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-723 id:cf-77-1 class:cf-77-1 \"Build on students\' strengths, and praise and reward them for successes, even when small\"]</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">&nbsp</div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-723 id:cf-77-1 class:cf-77-1 \"Involve families, students and community leaders in studying the content of the curriculum to determine whether it is relevant to the lives of the students\"]</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\"><b>Note: </b>To be most effective, continuously assess and make changes and additions to the curriculum to ensure that it is linked to students\' real lives</div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-723 id:cf-77-1 class:cf-77-1 \"Use song, drama, games and pictures to reinforce learning\"]</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">&nbsp</div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-723 id:cf-77-1 class:cf-77-1 \"Use clear language and encourage use of the mother tongue\"]</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">&nbsp</div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-723 id:cf-77-1 class:cf-77-1 \"Encourage teachers to make sure their face is well lit and that they face the children, not the blackboard, when speaking\"]</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">&nbsp</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n \n<p><b>5. Encourage flexibility in examinations and assessment</b></p>\n<p>This is one of the most challenging issues when promoting inclusion. Schools may not want children with learning difficulties to take exams, because it may reduce the schools average marks. Examination and assessment systems are often very rigid and inaccessible. There are, however, many examples of how children with disabilities and learning difficulties have managed to take part successfully in examinations and assessment.</p>\n<p>Some approaches are:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Use a \'scribe\', tapes or other audio facilities</li>\n<li>Give students with disabilities more time</li>\n<li>Assess students based on their strengths</li>\n<li>Use information and communication technology</li>\n<li>Use sign language interpreters, Braille or large print</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Often very bright children who have a disability are excluded from assessment and examinations. CBR can help create lobbying and advocacy groups to influence teachers and staff at different levels of the education system, emphasizing the rights of children with disabilities to participate without discrimination. The ultimate aim is to develop flexible, appropriate and accessible methods of assessment and examination. This, again, will help all children.</p>\n\n<p><b>6. Promote collaboration and support</b></p>\n<p>CBR can encourage peer collaboration and support by linking schools and teachers who are developing or implementing inclusive education. Other suggested activities include:</p>\n<div class=\"rTable\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-723 id:cf-77-1 class:cf-77-1 \"Encourage the recruitment of volunteers to help produce flexible curricula and teaching and learning aids to facilitate inclusive primary education\"]</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">Examples of potential volunteers:\n<ul>\n<li>Retired teachers</li>\n<li>Parents</li>\n<li>Other relatives</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-723 id:cf-77-1 class:cf-77-1 \"Encourage head teachers or teachers associations to share experiences and support inclusion\"]</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">Identify head teachers or others with positive experiences who may be willing to share: [textarea textarea-210 id:cf-255-1 class:cf-255-1]</div>\n</div>\n\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-723 id:cf-77-1 class:cf-77-1 \"Encourage the development of extracurricular activities and clubs to:\"]\n<ul>\n<li>Provide peer support</li>\n<li>Develop activities to raise awareness about disability</li>\n</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\"><b>Examples:</b>\n<ul>\n<li>Musical or theatre groups</li>\n<li>Craft clubs to create awareness posters</li>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-723 id:cf-77-1 class:cf-77-1 \"Identify role-models from disabled peoples organizations to work with schoolchildren\"]\n</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">Identify potential role-models from disabled peoples organizations:\n[textarea textarea-233 id:cf-255-1 class:cf-255-1]\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<br><button type=\"submit\" value=\"Submit\">Save</button>\n      <button type=\"reset\" value=\"Reset\">Print</button>\n</div>'),(2481,332,'_mail','a:9:{s:6:\"active\";b:1;s:7:\"subject\";s:25:\"INCLUDE: \"[your-subject]\"\";s:6:\"sender\";s:32:\"INCLUDE: <wordpress@include.xyz>\";s:9:\"recipient\";s:21:\"bomoxuxul@parcel4.net\";s:4:\"body\";s:165:\"From: [your-name] <[your-email]>\nSubject: [your-subject]\n\nMessage Body:\n[your-message]\n\n-- \nThis e-mail was sent from a contact form on INCLUDE: (http://include.xyz)\";s:18:\"additional_headers\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"attachments\";s:0:\"\";s:8:\"use_html\";b:0;s:13:\"exclude_blank\";b:0;}'),(2482,332,'_mail_2','a:9:{s:6:\"active\";b:0;s:7:\"subject\";s:25:\"INCLUDE: \"[your-subject]\"\";s:6:\"sender\";s:32:\"INCLUDE: <wordpress@include.xyz>\";s:9:\"recipient\";s:12:\"[your-email]\";s:4:\"body\";s:107:\"Message Body:\n[your-message]\n\n-- \nThis e-mail was sent from a contact form on INCLUDE: (http://include.xyz)\";s:18:\"additional_headers\";s:31:\"Reply-To: bomoxuxul@parcel4.net\";s:11:\"attachments\";s:0:\"\";s:8:\"use_html\";b:0;s:13:\"exclude_blank\";b:0;}'),(2483,332,'_messages','a:23:{s:12:\"mail_sent_ok\";s:45:\"Thank you for your message. It has been sent.\";s:12:\"mail_sent_ng\";s:71:\"There was an error trying to send your message. Please try again later.\";s:16:\"validation_error\";s:61:\"One or more fields have an error. Please check and try again.\";s:4:\"spam\";s:71:\"There was an error trying to send your message. Please try again later.\";s:12:\"accept_terms\";s:69:\"You must accept the terms and conditions before sending your message.\";s:16:\"invalid_required\";s:22:\"The field is required.\";s:16:\"invalid_too_long\";s:22:\"The field is too long.\";s:17:\"invalid_too_short\";s:23:\"The field is too short.\";s:12:\"invalid_date\";s:29:\"The date format is incorrect.\";s:14:\"date_too_early\";s:44:\"The date is before the earliest one allowed.\";s:13:\"date_too_late\";s:41:\"The date is after the latest one allowed.\";s:13:\"upload_failed\";s:46:\"There was an unknown error uploading the file.\";s:24:\"upload_file_type_invalid\";s:49:\"You are not allowed to upload files of this type.\";s:21:\"upload_file_too_large\";s:20:\"The file is too big.\";s:23:\"upload_failed_php_error\";s:38:\"There was an error uploading the file.\";s:14:\"invalid_number\";s:29:\"The number format is invalid.\";s:16:\"number_too_small\";s:47:\"The number is smaller than the minimum allowed.\";s:16:\"number_too_large\";s:46:\"The number is larger than the maximum allowed.\";s:23:\"quiz_answer_not_correct\";s:36:\"The answer to the quiz is incorrect.\";s:17:\"captcha_not_match\";s:31:\"Your entered code is incorrect.\";s:13:\"invalid_email\";s:38:\"The e-mail address entered is invalid.\";s:11:\"invalid_url\";s:19:\"The URL is invalid.\";s:11:\"invalid_tel\";s:32:\"The telephone number is invalid.\";}'),(2484,332,'_additional_settings',''),(2485,332,'_locale','en_US'),(2511,334,'_form','<div class=\"intro\"> \n<h5><b>Use available resources and develop support</b></h5>\n<p>Often times, there are resources and services already available in the community that are not fully used, or that could be extended to provide additional support for children, parents, and teachers. CBR should work to identify any such resources that may be available in the community and ensure that these resources are being used.</p>\n<p><em>Complete the following form to identify the support strategies you believe will work best in your situation. Select Save when you are finished.</em></p>\n\n<p><b>1. Draw on local resources and support</b></p>\n<p>Identify locally available resources that could be used to help create an effective learning environment for all children.</p>\n\n\n<div class=\"rTable\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">What is the attitude of the head teacher, \nclass teachers and other children towards children with disabilities?</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[textarea textarea-592 id:cf-140-1 class:textarea rows:4 cols:45]</div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">Are there children with disabilities already in school?</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[textarea textarea-592 id:cf-140-1 class:textarea rows:4 cols:45]</div>\n</div>\n\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">What percentage of the children in school are girls?</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[textarea textarea-592 id:cf-140-1 class:textarea rows:4 cols:45]</div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">What are the dropout, repeater and completion rates?\n</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[textarea textarea-592 id:cf-140-1 class:textarea rows:4 cols:45]</div>\n</div>\n\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">What is the quality of teaching and learning?</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[textarea textarea-592 id:cf-140-1 class:textarea rows:4 cols:45]</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">Are there any teachers with disabilities?</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[textarea textarea-592 id:cf-140-1 class:textarea rows:4 cols:45]</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">What barriers (in terms of resources, structures, or attitudes) get in the way of inclusive education?</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[textarea textarea-592 id:cf-140-1 class:textarea rows:4 cols:45]</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">Are there any other questions specific to your context that you want to ask at this stage?</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[textarea textarea-592 id:cf-140-1 class:textarea rows:4 cols:45]</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>By focusing on the whole-school system, CBR can help teachers understand what a social model approach to inclusion means in practice.</p>\n<p><b>2. Focus on quality</b></p>\n<p>Working to ensure equal access for children with disabilities is only one part of the inclusion process. What happens inside the classroom, such as quality of education, is extremely important. Poor teaching quality is very common, and often, large numbers of children may not be learning or participating. Working together to help children with disabilities learn often leads to an improved teaching and learning environment for all children.</p>\n<p>CBR programmes should encourage teachers to:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Be creative</li>\n<li>Solve problems together</li>\n<li>Use existing resources flexibly</li>\n<li>Observe what is happening</li>\n<li>Listen to children</li>\n<li>Build on the strengths of the students</li>\n<p>A whole-school approach is more effective than focusing on one particular teacher; and the head teachers support is crucial. Make sure to set time to work directly with the head teacher to gain support and buy-in, and to work with all teachers to brainstorm additional ideas.</p>\n\n<b>3. Provide training and support for teachers</b>\n<p>Often teachers have limited knowledge about children with disabilities. Ongoing training in the school environment is the most effective way to train teachers. CBR can develop and provide training and resources for a variety of topics, including:</p>\n\n<div class=\"rTable\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableHead p-2 vertical\"><strong>Topics</strong></div>\n<div class=\"rTableHead p-2 vertical\"><strong>Write your ideas here, if applicable for your community and context</strong></div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-723 id:cf-77-1 class:cf-77-1 \"Different impairments and their implications for learning\"]</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[textarea textarea-592 id:cf-140-1 class:textarea rows:4 cols:45]</div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-723 id:cf-77-1 class:cf-77-1 \"Different modes, means and forms of communication\"]</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[textarea textarea-592 id:cf-140-1 class:textarea rows:4 cols:45]</div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-723 id:cf-77-1 class:cf-77-1 \"Daily living skills, orientation and mobility skills\"]</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[textarea textarea-592 id:cf-140-1 class:textarea rows:4 cols:45]</div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-723 id:cf-77-1 class:cf-77-1 \"Assistive devices, teaching aids and equipment\"]</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[textarea textarea-592 id:cf-140-1 class:textarea rows:4 cols:45]</div>\n</div>\n\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-723 id:cf-77-1 class:cf-77-1 \"Monitoring and evaluation of inclusive primary education with the active involvement of children\"]</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[textarea textarea-592 id:cf-140-1 class:textarea rows:4 cols:45]</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p><b>4. Encourage change in curricula and teaching methods</b></p>\n<p>CBR can liaise between local primary schools, the community, non-governmental organizations and district education departments to assist teachers in making curricula flexible and teaching methods learner-centred. This will benefit all children.</p>\n<p>Usually local primary schools and CBR will have limited freedom to adapt the curriculum and teaching methods. In many countries, there are strict government controls. But small, simple changes are possible at the local level, and it may also be possible to lobby for change at the district and national levels. Examples of how curricula and teaching methods can become more flexible include:</p>\n\n<div class=\"rTable\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-723 id:cf-77-1 class:cf-77-1 \"Get children to work in small groups\"]</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">&nbsp</div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-723 id:cf-77-1 class:cf-77-1 \"Start a \'buddy\' system  putting children in pairs to support each other\"]</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\"><b>Examples: </b>Pair one child who has difficulty in learning with another child who learns more easily\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-723 id:cf-77-1 class:cf-77-1 \"Team teaching\"]</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\"><b>Note: </b>This can free up one adult to move around the class to help those who are having more difficulty.\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-723 id:cf-77-1 class:cf-77-1 \"Create learning aids and equipment out of local materials. This can help students with learning difficulties\"]</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\"><b>Examples: </b>\n<ul>\n<li>Sticks</li>\n<li>Stones</li>\n<li>Bottle tops</li>\n<li>Seeds</li>\n</ul></div>\n</div>\n\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-723 id:cf-77-1 class:cf-77-1 \"Seek the active participation of students, particularly children with disabilities, girls and those who seem to be less involved\"]</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">&nbsp</div>\n</div>\n\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-723 id:cf-77-1 class:cf-77-1 \"Build on students\' strengths, and praise and reward them for successes, even when small\"]</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">&nbsp</div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-723 id:cf-77-1 class:cf-77-1 \"Involve families, students and community leaders in studying the content of the curriculum to determine whether it is relevant to the lives of the students\"]</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\"><b>Note: </b>To be most effective, continuously assess and make changes and additions to the curriculum to ensure that it is linked to students\' real lives</div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-723 id:cf-77-1 class:cf-77-1 \"Use song, drama, games and pictures to reinforce learning\"]</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">&nbsp</div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-723 id:cf-77-1 class:cf-77-1 \"Use clear language and encourage use of the mother tongue\"]</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">&nbsp</div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-723 id:cf-77-1 class:cf-77-1 \"Encourage teachers to make sure their face is well lit and that they face the children, not the blackboard, when speaking\"]</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">&nbsp</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n \n<p><b>5. Encourage flexibility in examinations and assessment</b></p>\n<p>This is one of the most challenging issues when promoting inclusion. Schools may not want children with learning difficulties to take exams, because it may reduce the schools average marks. Examination and assessment systems are often very rigid and inaccessible. There are, however, many examples of how children with disabilities and learning difficulties have managed to take part successfully in examinations and assessment.</p>\n<p>Some approaches are:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Use a \'scribe\', tapes or other audio facilities</li>\n<li>Give students with disabilities more time</li>\n<li>Assess students based on their strengths</li>\n<li>Use information and communication technology</li>\n<li>Use sign language interpreters, Braille or large print</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Often very bright children who have a disability are excluded from assessment and examinations. CBR can help create lobbying and advocacy groups to influence teachers and staff at different levels of the education system, emphasizing the rights of children with disabilities to participate without discrimination. The ultimate aim is to develop flexible, appropriate and accessible methods of assessment and examination. This, again, will help all children.</p>\n\n<p><b>6. Promote collaboration and support</b></p>\n<p>CBR can encourage peer collaboration and support by linking schools and teachers who are developing or implementing inclusive education. Other suggested activities include:</p>\n<div class=\"rTable\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-723 id:cf-77-1 class:cf-77-1 \"Encourage the recruitment of volunteers to help produce flexible curricula and teaching and learning aids to facilitate inclusive primary education\"]</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">Examples of potential volunteers:\n<ul>\n<li>Retired teachers</li>\n<li>Parents</li>\n<li>Other relatives</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-723 id:cf-77-1 class:cf-77-1 \"Encourage head teachers or teachers associations to share experiences and support inclusion\"]</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">Identify head teachers or others with positive experiences who may be willing to share: [textarea textarea-210 id:cf-255-1 class:cf-255-1]</div>\n</div>\n\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-723 id:cf-77-1 class:cf-77-1 \"Encourage the development of extracurricular activities and clubs to:\"]\n<ul>\n<li>Provide peer support</li>\n<li>Develop activities to raise awareness about disability</li>\n</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\"><b>Examples:</b>\n<ul>\n<li>Musical or theatre groups</li>\n<li>Craft clubs to create awareness posters</li>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-723 id:cf-77-1 class:cf-77-1 \"Identify role-models from disabled peoples organizations to work with schoolchildren\"]\n</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">Identify potential role-models from disabled peoples organizations:\n[textarea textarea-233 id:cf-255-1 class:cf-255-1]\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<br><button type=\"submit\" value=\"Submit\">Save</button>\n      <button type=\"reset\" value=\"Reset\">Print</button>\n</div>'),(2512,334,'_mail','a:9:{s:6:\"active\";b:1;s:7:\"subject\";s:25:\"INCLUDE: \"[your-subject]\"\";s:6:\"sender\";s:32:\"INCLUDE: <wordpress@include.xyz>\";s:9:\"recipient\";s:21:\"bomoxuxul@parcel4.net\";s:4:\"body\";s:165:\"From: [your-name]