mmes offer excellent opportunities for people with disabilities to be educated alongside their non-disabled peers.</p>\n<p>CBR can identify existing non-formal education programmes and encourage them to become inclusive of people with disabilities.</p>\n<p><em>Complete the following form to identify the support strategies you believe will work best in your situation. Select <b>Save</b> when you are finished.</em></p>\n<b>Identify existing programmes</b>\n<p>Begin by identifying non-formal education programmes that are already operating in your community.</p>\n<p>Non-formal education programmes are often oriented towards literacy and basic education, health promotion, such as reproductive health issues, sexually transmitted diseases, HIV and AIDS, environmental issues, agriculture, fishing, rural development and community development.</p>\n<p>Determine whether each programme is currently accessible and inclusive of people with disabilities and, if not, list modification(s) needed to enable the programme to become accessible and inclusive.</p>\n\n<div class=\"rTable\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableHead p-2 vertical\"><strong>Programme</strong></div>\n<div class=\"rTableHead p-2 vertical\"><strong>Educational focus</strong></div>\n<div class=\"rTableHead p-2 vertical\"><strong>Contact information</strong></div>\n<div class=\"rTableHead p-2 vertical\"><strong>Accessible/ inclusive of people with disabilities?</strong></div>\n<div class=\"rTableHead p-2 vertical\"><strong>Modifications needed</strong></div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[text text-897 id:text11 class:text12 class:w-100]</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[text text-897 id:text11 class:text12 class:w-100]</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[text text-897 id:text11 class:text12 class:w-100]</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[text text-897 id:text11 class:text12 class:w-100]</div>\n<div 