b>1. Collect information</b></p>\n<b>Survey the labour market</b>\n<p>Collect accurate and up-to-date information on the local labour market. Already-existing information can often be obtained by contacting sources like the following:</p>\n[checkbox checkbox-629 id:checkbox class:checkbox12 \"The local chamber of commerce\"]\n[checkbox checkbox-629 id:checkbox class:checkbox12 \"Relevant government agencies (e.g. the ministry of labour)\"]\n\n<p>Employment opportunities can also be identified through simple research. Contact local enterprises directly and inquire about:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Their need for workers</li>\n<li>The supply of workers available to fill these jobs</li>\n</ul>\n<b>Identify available support services</b>\n<p>Identify referral and support services that can assist people with disabilities in finding wage employment. Where services do not exist, CBR should consider providing them.</p>\n<b>Career counselling services</b>\n\n<b>2. Identify potential allies</b>\n<p>Identify and contact businesses that already have a proactive policy of employing people with disabilities and use them as examples.</p>\n\n<b>Career counselling services</b>\n\n<div class=\"rTable\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableHead p-2 vertical\"><b>Name</b></div>\n<div class=\"rTableHead p-2 vertical\"><b>Location</b></div>\n<div class=\"rTableHead p-2 vertical\"><b>Contact name</b></div>\n<div class=\"rTableHead p-2 vertical\"><b>Contact Information</b></div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2\">[text text-15 id:cf-265-1 class:cf-265-1 class:w-100]</div> \n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2\">[text text-15 id:cf-265-1 class:cf-265-1 class:w-100]</div> \n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2\">[text text-15 id:cf-265-1 class:cf-265-1 class:w-100]</div> \n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2\">[text text-15 id:cf-265-1 class:cf-265-1 class:w-100]</div> \n</div>\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2\">[text text-15 id:cf-265-1