"invalid_url\";s:19:\"The URL is invalid.\";s:11:\"invalid_tel\";s:32:\"The telephone number is invalid.\";}'),(3027,407,'_additional_settings',''),(3028,407,'_locale','en_US'),(3035,409,'_form','<div class=\"intro\"> \n<h5><b>Support workers with disabilities to retain employment</b></h5>\n<p>Providing assistance in finding employment is an important first step, but individuals with disability also often require support to ensure that they will be able to retain their jobs. Families, friends and neighbours and friends can provide some forms of support, but CBR programmes should also be prepared to link workers with disabilities with other, more formal forms of support.</p>\n<p><em>CBR workers can use this form to think through how to provide such support to an individual who needs it. Complete the form now using the example of an individual with disability with whom you are already familiar. Select <b>Save</b> when you are finished.</em></p>\n<p>Once a worker with disabilities is employed, CBR programmes can ensure the availability of a support worker, job coach, staff member, union volunteer or mentor to provide ongoing support to:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Help ensure that necessary adjustments to the workplace are made</li>\n<li>Assist the employer and worker to solve any problems that might arise, and</li>\n<li>Ensure that the worker is performing adequately in the job</li>\n</ul>\n<p>To assist in this effort, CBR programmes should consider making periodic visits to employees on the job to determine how things are going and if help is needed.</p>\n<p>Individuals willing to provide support:</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"rTable\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableHead p-2 vertical\"><b>Name</b></div>\n<div class=\"rTableHead p-2 vertical\"><b>Role</b></div>\n<div class=\"rTableHead p-2 vertical\"><b>Contact Information</b></div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2\">[text text-15 id:cf-265-1 class:cf-265-1 class