 and responsibilities, and with little or no support. This often leaves them exhausted with little time for their own needs. CBR should make every effort to provide support for family members whenever possible.</p>\n<p><i>Complete the following form to identify the support strategies you believe will work best in your situation. Select <b>Save</b> when you are finished.</i></p>\n<p>Begin by listening and talking with family members to identify their concerns; then work with them to identify options for addressing these concerns, including the following.</p>\n<p><b>Link family members to others in similar situations</b></p>\n<p>Family members can often benefit from establishing relationships with others who are in similar situations. Simply being able to share feelings and experiences with others who understand can be extremely helpful; and often those with similar concerns are able to provide one another more concrete forms of support, such as shared caretaking arrangements.</p>\n<p>Linking family members to self-help groups, disabled peoples organizations and parents or family organizations is an effective way to establish these connections. Identify these types of organizations that exist in the communities your organization serves below.</p>\n\n\n<div class=\"rTable\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableHead p-2 w-25\"><strong>Organization name</strong></div>\n<div class=\"rTableHead p-2 w-25\"><strong>Organization type</strong></div>\n<div class=\"rTableHead p-2 w-25\"><strong>Member concerns</strong></div>\n<div class=\"rTableHead p-2 w-25\"><strong>Contact Information</strong></div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical w-25\">[textarea textarea-187 id:textarea1 class:textarea cols:25 rows:5 class:w-100]</div>\n\n\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 w-25\">\n<div class=\"p-1\">[checkbox checkbox-614 id:checkbox55 class:checkbox \"Disabled peoples organization\"]</div>\n<div class=\"p-1\">[checkbo