"width: 100%;\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">Local government grants or subsidies *</div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical \">[textarea textarea-183 id:textarea3 cols:50 rows:5]<br/></div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">Local business donations and corporate sponsorships </div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical \">[textarea textarea-183 id:textarea3 cols:50 rows:5]<br/></div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">Civil society organizations (e.g. Rotary Club, Lions Club)</div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical \">[textarea textarea-183 id:textarea3 cols:50 rows:5]<br/></div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">Service fees or user charges (for clients with the necessary means)</div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical \">[textarea textarea-183 id:textarea3 cols:50 rows:5]<br/></div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">Special events (e.g. raffles, social events, competitions)</div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical \">[textarea textarea-183 id:textarea3 cols:50 rows:5]<br/></div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">Income-generating activities</div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical \">[textarea textarea-183 id:textarea3 cols:50 rows:5]<br/></div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">Microfinance or a community-based revolving fund</div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical \">[textarea textarea-183 id:textarea3 cols:50 rows:5]<br/></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>* It is important to work with government officials to ensure that CBR funding is provided for in all budgets.</p>\r\n<p><b>Financial management:</b> Establishing a transparent system for managing finances is very important. This will ensure that your programme is accountable to stakeholders, including funding bodies, community members and people with disabilities themselves. Financial management is a key role of the programme manager, but others may be involved, particularly when programmes are large and involve large amounts of money.</p>\r\n<p>Good financial management requires that the following tasks be completed:</p>\r\n<p>[checkbox checkbox-235 id:checkbox01 class:check1] Implement a mechanism to verify that all expenditures are related to planned activities</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n[checkbox checkbox-263 id:checkbox111 class:check \"Implement a mechanism to verify that all expenditures are related to planned activities\"]<br>\r\n[checkbox checkbox-263 id:checkbox111 class:check11 \"Maintain financial records regularly and adequately\"]<br>\r\n[checkbox checkbox-263 id:checkbox111 class:check12 \"Implement systems for appropriate checks and balances\"]<br>\r\n[checkbox checkbox-263 id:checkbox111 class:check13 \"Report regularly on the financial status of the programme\"]<br>\r\n\r\n<p><b>2. Human resources</b></p>\r\n<p><b>Recruiting:</b> It is strongly recommended that you follow these guidelines when recruiting CBR managers and personnel:</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTable\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical w-50\">[checkbox checkbox-263 id:checkbox111 class:check13 \"Prepare job descriptions for each position\"]<br>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\"><p><b>Note:</b> The job description for each position should specify:<br>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The roles and responsibilities, and\r\n</li>\r\n<li>The experience required\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</p><br>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-263 id:checkbox111 class:check13 \"Seek to hire staff members from the local community\"]<br>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\"><p><b>Note:</b> Individuals from the local community already possess:<br>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Good knowledge of the local culture and language\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Access to community members</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</p><br>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-263 id:checkbox111 class:check13 \"Whenever possible, recruit people with disabilities or their family members\"]<br>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\"><p><b>Note:</b> This:<br>The job description for each position should specify:<br>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Demonstrates a commitment to the principles of CBR\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Contributes to the empowerment of people with disabilities and their families\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</p><br>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-263 id:checkbox111 class:check13 \"Consider recruiting volunteers (particularly where resources are limited)\"]<br>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\"><p><b>Note:</b> When considering the use of volunteers, be sure to weigh both the advantages (volunteers usually have good local knowledge and are cost-effective) and disadvantages (they often have limited time, and turnover can be high).</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Training:</b> CBR programme managers and personnel require a wide range of knowledge and skills to enable them to carry out their roles and responsibilities, so it is important to do the following:</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTable\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-263 id:checkbox111 class:check13 \"Work to ensure that training standards are in place to ensure a minimum level of competency throughout the CBR community\"]</div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">&nbsp</div> \r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTable\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-263 id:checkbox111 class:check13 \"Identify training opportunities for <b>all CBR personnel</b> that cover the following topics:\"]</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">Existing training programmes:</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTable\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-263 id:checkbox111 class:check13 \"Work to ensure that training standards are in place to ensure a minimum level of competency throughout the CBR community\"]</div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">&nbsp</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-263 id:checkbox111 class:check13 \"Identify training opportunities for <b>all CBR personnel</b> that cover the following topics:\"]<br>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Disability rights</li>\r\n<li>Community development</li>\r\n<li>Inclusive practices</li>\r\n<li>Communication</li>\r\n<li>Basic rehabilitation skills (e.g. identification, basic screening and assessment, basic therapy activities)</li>\r\n<li>Group processes (e.g. setting up self-help groups)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">Existing training programmes:</div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow style=\"width: 100%;\">Programme <br>[text text-697 id:text01 class:text]<br>[text text-697 id:text02 class:text]<br>[text text-697 id:text03 class:text]<br>[text text-697 id:text04 class:text]</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow style=\"width: 100%;\">Contact info<br>[text text-697 id:text01 class:text]<br>[text text-697 id:text02 class:text]<br>[text text-697 id:text03 class:text]<br>[text text-697 id:text04 class:text]</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br><button type=\"submit\" value=\"Submit\">Save</button>\r\n      <button type=\"reset\" value=\"Reset\">Print</button>\r\n</div>\n1\nINCLUDE: \"[your-subject]\"\nINCLUDE: <wordpress@include.xyz>\nbomoxuxul@parcel4.net\nFrom: [your-name] <[your-email]>\r\nSubject: [your-subject]\r\n\r\nMessage Body:\r\n[your-message]\r\n\r\n-- \r\nThis e-mail was sent from a contact form on INCLUDE: (http://include.xyz)\n\n\n\n\n\nINCLUDE: \"[your-subject]\"\nINCLUDE: <wordpress@include.xyz>\n[your-email]\nMessage Body:\r\n[your-message]\r\n\r\n-- \r\nThis e-mail was sent from a contact form on INCLUDE: (http://include.xyz)\nReply-To: bomoxuxul@parcel4.net\n\n\n\nThank you for your message. It has been sent.\nThere was an error trying to send your message. Please try again later.\nOne or more fields have an error. Please check and try again.\nThere was an error trying to send your message. Please try again later.\nYou must accept the terms and conditions before sending your message.\nThe field is required.\nThe field is too long.\nThe field is too short.\nThe date format is incorrect.\nThe date is before the earliest one allowed.\nThe date is after the latest one allowed.\nThere was an unknown error uploading the file.\nYou are not allowed to upload files of this type.\nThe file is too big.\nThere was an error uploading the file.\nThe number format is invalid.\nThe number is smaller than the minimum allowed.\nThe number is larger than the maximum allowed.\nThe answer to the quiz is incorrect.\nYour entered code is incorrect.\nThe e-mail address entered is invalid.\nThe URL is invalid.\nThe telephone number is invalid.','Mobilize and manage resources','','publish','closed','closed','','untitled-6','','','2019-06-21 08:09:52','2019-06-21 08:09:52','',0,'http://include.xyz/?post_type=wpcf7_contact_form&#038;p=82',0,'wpcf7_contact_form','',0),(83,1,'2019-05-03 06:41:02','2019-05-03 06:41:02','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>To view or modify an activity in your action plan, use your mouse or keyboard to expand the module heading that contains the activity you want. Then select the activity name from the list that appears on the left-hand side of the screen.</em>[contact-form-7 id=\"82\" title=\"Untitled\"]<br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','My action plan','','inherit','closed','closed','','42-revision-v1','','','2019-05-03 06:41:02','2019-05-03 06:41:02','',42,'http://include.xyz/2019/05/03/42-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(84,1,'2019-05-06 05:27:19','2019-05-06 05:27:19','<div class=\"intro\"> \r\n<h3>Carry out planned activities</h3>\r\n<p>CBR programme managers need to be very familiar with their organizations work plans and be able to make the necessary preparations to ensure that all the activities are carried out as planned.\r\n</p>\r\n<p><i>The checklist below identifies general activities that nearly every CBR programme will undertake. Select Save when you are finished.</i></p>\r\n<p>General activities that are undertaken by nearly every CBR programme include:</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTable\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-263 id:checkbox111 class:check13 \"\r\n <b>Awareness-raising </b> activities directed at stakeholders\"]<br>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\"><p><b>Note:</b> The goals of awareness-raising are to<br>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Provide information and knowledge about disability</li>\r\n<li>Generate attitudinal and behaviour change</li>\r\n<li>Generate support for the CBR strategy and programmes</li>\r\n<li>Encourage stakeholder involvement and participation</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</p>\r\n<br>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-263 id:checkbox111 class:check13 \"<b>Coordinating and networking</b> with stakeholders\"]<br>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\"><p><b>Note:</b> The goals are to:<br>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Build good relationships and partnerships</li>\r\n<li>Share knowledge and resources</li>\r\n<li>Reduce duplication of effort</li>\r\n<li>Mobilize community resources</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</p>\r\n<br>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-263 id:checkbox111 class:check13 \"<b>Mainstreaming</b> activities\"]<br>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\"><p><b>Note:</b> The goal is to ensure that people with disabilities are able to fully participate and are supported in each development sector.<br>\r\n<p>Mainstreaming activities are accompanied by specific measures (e.g. reasonable accommodation to ensure access to equal opportunities).\r\n</p>\r\n<br>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-263 id:checkbox111 class:check13 \"<b>Providing services</b>\"]<br>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\"><p><b>Note:</b>Each programme will provide a different range of services, which may include:<br>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Identification of people with disabilities</li>\r\n<li>Referrals to mainstream/specialized services</li>\r\n<li>Reduce duplication of effort</li>\r\n<li>Providing basic rehabilitation</li>\r\n<li>Providing simple assistive devices</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</p>\r\n<br>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-263 id:checkbox111 class:check13 \"<b>Advocacy </b> activities\"]<br>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\"><p><b>Note:</b>Many different types of advocacy activities can be used to ensure that equal opportunities and rights for people with disabilities are achieved in every aspect of community life. Among the tools that can be used to increase social accountability are:<br>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Social audits</li>\r\n<li>Community score cards</li>\r\n<li>Citizen report cards</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</p>\r\n<br>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-263 id:checkbox111 class:check13 \"<b>Capacity building</b> activities (to ensure that stakeholders possess the knowledge and skills required to carry out their roles and responsibilities)\"]<br>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\"><p><b>Existing training programmes for stakeholders:</b></p><br>[text text-286 id:text01 class:textbox]<br><br>[text text-286 id:text02 class:textbox]<br><br>[text text-286 id:text02 class:textbox]<br>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br><button type=\"submit\" value=\"Submit\">Save</button>\r\n      <button type=\"reset\" value=\"Reset\">Print</button>\r\n</div>\n1\nINCLUDE: \"[your-subject]\"\nINCLUDE: <wordpress@include.xyz>\nbomoxuxul@parcel4.net\nFrom: [your-name] <[your-email]>\r\nSubject: [your-subject]\r\n\r\nMessage Body:\r\n[your-message]\r\n\r\n-- \r\nThis e-mail was sent from a contact form on INCLUDE: (http://include.xyz)\n\n\n\n\n\nINCLUDE: \"[your-subject]\"\nINCLUDE: <wordpress@include.xyz>\n[your-email]\nMessage Body:\r\n[your-message]\r\n\r\n-- \r\nThis e-mail was sent from a contact form on INCLUDE: (http://include.xyz)\nReply-To: bomoxuxul@parcel4.net\n\n\n\nThank you for your message. It has been sent.\nThere was an error trying to send your message. Please try again later.\nOne or more fields have an error. Please check and try again.\nThere was an error trying to send your message. Please try again later.\nYou must accept the terms and conditions before sending your message.\nThe field is required.\nThe field is too long.\nThe field is too short.\nThe date format is incorrect.\nThe date is before the earliest one allowed.\nThe date is after the latest one allowed.\nThere was an unknown error uploading the file.\nYou are not allowed to upload files of this type.\nThe file is too big.\nThere was an error uploading the file.\nThe number format is invalid.\nThe number is smaller than the minimum allowed.\nThe number is larger than the maximum allowed.\nThe answer to the quiz is incorrect.\nYour entered code is incorrect.\nThe e-mail address entered is invalid.\nThe URL is invalid.\nThe telephone number is invalid.','Carry out planned activities','','publish','closed','closed','','untitled-7','','','2019-05-06 07:17:48','2019-05-06 07:17:48','',0,'http://include.xyz/?post_type=wpcf7_contact_form&#038;p=84',0,'wpcf7_contact_form','',0),(86,1,'2019-05-06 05:30:34','2019-05-06 05:30:34','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>To view or modify an activity in your action plan, use your mouse or keyboard to expand the module heading that contains the activity you want. Then select the activity name from the list that appears on the left-hand side of the screen.</em>[contact-form-7 id=\"84\" title=\"Untitled\"]<br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','My action plan','','inherit','closed','closed','','42-revision-v1','','','2019-05-06 05:30:34','2019-05-06 05:30:34','',42,'http://include.xyz/2019/05/06/42-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(87,1,'2019-05-06 08:48:45','2019-05-06 08:48:45','<div class=\"intro\"> \r\n<h3>Monitor programme activities</h3>\r\n<p>Monitoring involves the regular collection and analysis of information of programme activities. The monitoring process helps the CBR team identify which activities are going well and which are not, so that the necessary changes can be made. When good monitoring systems are in place and are effective, evaluation of the programme becomes much easier.\r\n</p>\r\n<p><i>Complete the following checklist as a first step in planning your monitoring process. Select <b>Save</b> when you are finished.</i></p>\r\n<p>The following steps are involved in monitoring a programme:</p>\r\n<p><b>1. Set indicators</b></p>\r\n<p>The indicators were defined earlier, during the <b>Planning and design</b> stage.</p>\r\n<p><b>2. Decide how to collect information</b></p>\r\n<p>The methods for collecting monitoring data were defined earlier, in the <b>Programme plan.</b></p>\r\n<p><b>3. Collect and record information:</b></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTable\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-263 id:checkbox111 class:check13 \"\r\n Put in place formal systems for collecting and recording information\"]<br>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\"><p><b>Note:</b> Data collection systems should:<br>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Be as simple as possible</li>\r\n<li>Collect only the information that is required</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<br>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-263 id:checkbox111 class:check13 \"\r\nInstitute a regular data collection schedule\"]<br>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\"><p><b>Note:</b>Depending on the needs of your programme, schedules may be:<br>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Daily</li>\r\n<li>Weekly</li>\r\n<li>Monthly, and/or</li>\r\n<li>Quarterly</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-263 id:checkbox111 class:check13 \"\r\nTrain all staff members in the use of these systems\"]<br>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p><b>4. Analyze information</b></p>\r\n<p>Collecting and recording information is often much easier than analyzing it. However, if CBR programme managers do not look closely at the information, they will not be able to observe the progress of the programme activities and identify any potential problems.</p><br>\r\n<p>To conduct an effective analysis, you will need to:</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-263 id:checkbox111 class:check13 \"Summarize the data\"]<br>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\"><p><b>Note:</b>This may require aggregating data from multiple sources<br>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-263 id:checkbox111 class:check13 \"Identify trends in the data\"]<br>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-263 id:checkbox111 class:check13 \"Recognize what the trends suggest\"]<br>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-263 id:checkbox111 class:check13 \"Discuss the findings with key stakeholders\"]<br>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><b>5. Report and share information:</b></p>\r\n<p>Reporting and sharing the results of monitoring with key stakeholders shows that the programme is transparent and accountable. A monitoring report should include information on:</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-263 id:checkbox111 class:check13 \"The activity or work area being reported on\"]<br>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-263 id:checkbox111 class:check13 \"Work planned for the period vs. work completed\"]<br>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-263 id:checkbox111 class:check13 \"Progress towards the programme outcomes\"]<br>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-263 id:checkbox111 class:check13 \"Budgeted vs. actual expenditures\"]<br>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-263 id:checkbox111 class:check13 \" Achievements\"]<br>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-263 id:checkbox111 class:check13 \"Constraints/problems\"]<br>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-263 id:checkbox111 class:check13 \"Actions taken or recommended\"]<br>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-263 id:checkbox111 class:check13 \"Lessons learnt\"]<br>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>Reporting requirements will vary depending on the management structures in place for CBR programmes. For example, at the local level, CBR personnel may need to report to the programme manager on a weekly basis, while programme managers may need to report to higher levels on a monthly basis, and so on.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><b>6. Manage the information</b></p>\r\n<p>A CBR programme can generate a lot of information (e.g. documents, reports, correspondence and written accounts). You will need to develop an effective system for managing all of this information.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-263 id:checkbox111 class:check13 \"Create an efficient filing system\"]<br>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\"><p><b>Note:</b> Having an efficient system will save a great deal of time and prevent misunderstandings during monitoring<br>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-263 id:checkbox111 class:check13 \"Store any confidential information being collected in a secure location\"]<br>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-263 id:checkbox111 class:check13 \"Train all CBR staff in the proper procedures to follow when handling confidential information\"]<br>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\"><p><b>Note:</b> These include:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Locking storage cabinets and office doors</li>\r\n<li>Using strong passwords and encryption to protect data stored on computers</li>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br><button type=\"submit\" value=\"Submit\">Save</button>\r\n      <button type=\"reset\" value=\"Reset\">Print</button>\r\n</div>\n1\nINCLUDE: \"[your-subject]\"\nINCLUDE: <wordpress@include.xyz>\nbomoxuxul@parcel4.net\nFrom: [your-name] <[your-email]>\r\nSubject: [your-subject]\r\n\r\nMessage Body:\r\n[your-message]\r\n\r\n-- \r\nThis e-mail was sent from a contact form on INCLUDE: (http://include.xyz)\n\n\n\n\n\nINCLUDE: \"[your-subject]\"\nINCLUDE: <wordpress@include.xyz>\n[your-email]\nMessage Body:\r\n[your-message]\r\n\r\n-- \r\nThis e-mail was sent from a contact form on INCLUDE: (http://include.xyz)\nReply-To: bomoxuxul@parcel4.net\n\n\n\nThank you for your message. It has been sent.\nThere was an error trying to send your message. Please try again later.\nOne or more fields have an error. Please check and try again.\nThere was an error trying to send your message. Please try again later.\nYou must accept the terms and conditions before sending your message.\nThe field is required.\nThe field is too long.\nThe field is too short.\nThe date format is incorrect.\nThe date is before the earliest one allowed.\nThe date is after the latest one allowed.\nThere was an unknown error uploading the file.\nYou are not allowed to upload files of this type.\nThe file is too big.\nThere was an error uploading the file.\nThe number format is invalid.\nThe number is smaller than the minimum allowed.\nThe number is larger than the maximum allowed.\nThe answer to the quiz is incorrect.\nYour entered code is incorrect.\nThe e-mail address entered is invalid.\nThe URL is invalid.\nThe telephone number is invalid.','Monitor programme activities','','publish','closed','closed','','monitor-programme-activities','','','2019-05-06 09:47:38','2019-05-06 09:47:38','',0,'http://include.xyz/?post_type=wpcf7_contact_form&#038;p=87',0,'wpcf7_contact_form','',0),(88,1,'2019-05-06 08:49:15','2019-05-06 08:49:15','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>To view or modify an activity in your action plan, use your mouse or keyboard to expand the module heading that contains the activity you want. Then select the activity name from the list that appears on the left-hand side of the screen.</em>[contact-form-7 id=\"87\" title=\"Monitor programme activities\"]<br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','My action plan','','inherit','closed','closed','','42-revision-v1','','','2019-05-06 08:49:15','2019-05-06 08:49:15','',42,'http://include.xyz/2019/05/06/42-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(89,1,'2019-05-06 11:54:28','2019-05-06 11:54:28','<div class=\"intro\"> \r\n<h3>Focus the evaluation</h3>\r\n<p>AThe first step of the evaluation stage involves:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Deciding what the focus of the evaluation will be (i.e. the purpose of the evaluation), and</li>\r\n<li>Making a decision about the questions you want the evaluation to answer\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>CBR personnel, people with disabilities, representatives from disabled peoples organizations and other key stakeholders should all participate in these decisions.\r\n</p>\r\n<p><i>Complete the following form to start this process. Select Save when you are finished.</i></p>\r\n<p><b>Purpose</b></p>\r\n<p>It is not possible for one evaluation to assess all aspects of a CBR programme. Therefore it is important to think carefully about the purpose of the evaluation. The table below lists a few possible purposes:</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTable\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\"><b>You might want to assess</b>	\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\"><b>To help you</b>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">Whether CBR personnel are able to carry out their roles and responsibilities competently</div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">Decide whether staff members require further training\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">Which activities worked best	</div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">Determine which aspects of the programme should be continued or discontinued\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">Whether the programme is having the planned impact		</div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">Decide whether to replicate the strategy elsewhere\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">Whether: \r\n<ul><li>Resources have been used as originally planned</li>\r\n<li>Outcomes have been achieved, and</li>\r\n<li>Procedures have been followed\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">Make decisions about the future of the programme\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>Identify the purpose of your evaluation below:\r\n<br>[textarea textarea-412 id:textarea01 class:textarea cols:60 rows:5]</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Questions to answer</b></p>\r\n<p>Once the purpose of the evaluation has been identified, it is then possible to develop the key questions that the evaluation will need to answer. Many different questions can be asked, relating to the relevance, efficiency, effectiveness, impact and sustainability of the programme (see examples below).</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\"><b>Relevance</b></div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">Does the programme meet the needs of people with disabilities, their families and their community?\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\"><b>Efficiency	</b></div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">Have the resources (human, financial and material) been used in the best way?\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\"><b>Effectiveness</b></div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">Did the programme achieve its outcomes in terms of quality, quantity and time?\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\"><b>Impact</b></div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">Has the wider goal been achieved? In what ways has the programme changed the lives of people with disabilities and their families? What effect has the programme had on the community in terms of its attitudes and behaviour towards people with disabilities?\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\"><b>Sustainability</b></div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">Will the programme be able to continue when external support is scaled down or withdrawn?\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>Now identify the key questions that your evaluation will need to answer:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>[text text-18 id:text1 class:text]</li><br>\r\n<li>[text text-18 id:text2 class:text]</li><br>\r\n<li>[text text-18 id:text3 class:text]</li><br>\r\n<li>[text text-18 id:text4 class:text]</li><br>\r\n<li>[text text-18 id:text5 class:text]</li><br>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br><button type=\"submit\" value=\"Submit\">Save</button>\r\n      <button type=\"reset\" value=\"Reset\">Print</button>\r\n</div>\n1\nINCLUDE: \"[your-subject]\"\nINCLUDE: <wordpress@include.xyz>\nbomoxuxul@parcel4.net\nFrom: [your-name] <[your-email]>\r\nSubject: [your-subject]\r\n\r\nMessage Body:\r\n[your-message]\r\n\r\n-- \r\nThis e-mail was sent from a contact form on INCLUDE: (http://include.xyz)\n\n\n\n\n\nINCLUDE: \"[your-subject]\"\nINCLUDE: <wordpress@include.xyz>\n[your-email]\nMessage Body:\r\n[your-message]\r\n\r\n-- \r\nThis e-mail was sent from a contact form on INCLUDE: (http://include.xyz)\nReply-To: bomoxuxul@parcel4.net\n\n\n\nThank you for your message. It has been sent.\nThere was an error trying to send your message. Please try again later.\nOne or more fields have an error. Please check and try again.\nThere was an error trying to send your message. Please try again later.\nYou must accept the terms and conditions before sending your message.\nThe field is required.\nThe field is too long.\nThe field is too short.\nThe date format is incorrect.\nThe date is before the earliest one allowed.\nThe date is after the latest one allowed.\nThere was an unknown error uploading the file.\nYou are not allowed to upload files of this type.\nThe file is too big.\nThere was an error uploading the file.\nThe number format is invalid.\nThe number is smaller than the minimum allowed.\nThe number is larger than the maximum allowed.\nThe answer to the quiz is incorrect.\nYour entered code is incorrect.\nThe e-mail address entered is invalid.\nThe URL is invalid.\nThe telephone number is invalid.','Focus the evaluation','','publish','closed','closed','','focus-the-evaluation','','','2019-05-09 05:39:43','2019-05-09 05:39:43','',0,'http://include.xyz/?post_type=wpcf7_contact_form&#038;p=89',0,'wpcf7_contact_form','',0),(90,1,'2019-05-06 11:55:00','2019-05-06 11:55:00','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>To view or modify an activity in your action plan, use your mouse or keyboard to expand the module heading that contains the activity you want. Then select the activity name from the list that appears on the left-hand side of the screen.</em>[contact-form-7 id=\"89\" title=\"Focus the evaluation\"]<br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','My action plan','','inherit','closed','closed','','42-revision-v1','','','2019-05-06 11:55:00','2019-05-06 11:55:00','',42,'http://include.xyz/2019/05/06/42-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(91,1,'2019-05-06 12:58:52','2019-05-06 12:58:52','<div class=\"intro\"> \r\n<h3>Carry out planned activities</h3>\r\n<p>The second step involves making a decision about the best way to answer the evaluation questions, thinking about the following issues:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Who can provide the information?</li>\r\n<li>How can the information be collected?</li>\r\n<li>When should it be collected?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><i>Complete this form to plan how and when to collect information. Select <b>Save</b> when you are finished.</i></p>\r\n<p><b>Who can provide the information?</b></p>\r\n<p>Select who can provide the information you need:</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTable\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-263 id:checkbox111 class:check13 \"\r\n People with disabilities and their families\"]<br>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-263 id:checkbox111 class:check13 \"\r\n Other stakeholders\"]<br>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-263 id:checkbox111 class:check13 \"\r\n CBR personnel\"]<br>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-263 id:checkbox111 class:check13 \"\r\n Other community programmes\"]<br>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-263 id:checkbox111 class:check13 \"\r\n Government authorities\"]\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\"><p><b>Examples:</b> National statistics office\r\n</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p><b>How can information be collected?</b></p>\r\n<p>Next, identify how the information will be collected. (Usually more than one method is used to collect information for an evaluation.)</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-263 id:checkbox111 class:check13 \"\r\n Expense records\"]\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\"><p><b>Note:</b> Can be used to:</p>\r\n<ul><li>Determine whether resources have been used as originally planned\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Provide assurance to funders that the programme is transparent and accountable\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-263 id:checkbox111 class:check13 \"\r\n Questionnaires\"]\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-263 id:checkbox111 class:check13 \"\r\nIndividual assessments\"]\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\"><p><b>Note:</b> Can be used to assess individuals current state of well-being, health, daily activities, etc.\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-263 id:checkbox111 class:check13 \"\r\nSurveys\"]\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\"><p><b>Note:</b>Can be used to assess attitudinal changes and quality-of-life changes (especially when compared with baseline data)\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-263 id:checkbox111 class:check13 \"\r\n Documentation reviews\"]\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\"><p><b>Note:</b> Can help to understand:</p>\r\n<ul><li>The policies underlying the programme</li>\r\n<li>How the programme operates</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-263 id:checkbox111 class:check13 \"\r\nRecord reviews\"]\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\"><p><b>Note:</b> Can provide an overview of:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The number and characteristics of clients</li>\r\n<li>The progress made</li>\r\n<li>The interventions made</li>\r\n<li>The relationship between inputs and results</li>\r\n<li>The workload of the rehabilitation workers</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-263 id:checkbox111 class:check13 \"\r\n Interviews\"]\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\"><p><b>Note:</b> Can help to:</p>\r\n<ul><li>Understand an individuals views, impressions or experiences</li>\r\n<li>Learn more about individuals answers to questionnaires</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-263 id:checkbox111 class:check13 \"\r\n Observation\"]\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\"><p><b>Note:</b>Can be used to gather accurate information about how a programme actually operates, particularly about processes and interactions\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-263 id:checkbox111 class:check13 \"\r\n Focus groups\"]\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\"><p><b>Note:</b>Can be used to explore a topic in depth through group discussion  for example:<br>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>To learn about reactions to an experience or suggestion</li>\r\n<li>To reach a common understanding of problems and issues</li>\r\n\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-263 id:checkbox111 class:check13 \"\r\n Public meetings\"]\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\"><p><b>Note:</b>Can be used to:\r\n<br>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Gather information from a wide range of sources</li>\r\n<li>Break down the distance between all citizens</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p><b>When should information be collected?</b></p>\r\n<p>Information can be collected at different stages.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-263 id:checkbox111 class:check13 \"\r\n Before a programme starts\"]\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\"><p><b>Note:</b>Provides baseline data that can be used to measure the impact a CBR programme has had.<br>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-263 id:checkbox111 class:check13 \"\r\n While the programme is underway\"]\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\"><p><b>Note:</b> Can be used to make adjustments to activities and processes.<br>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-263 id:checkbox111 class:check13 \"\r\nAt the end of the programme\"]\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\"><p><b>Note:</b>When compared with baseline data, indicates the impact the programme has had.<br>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br><button type=\"submit\" value=\"Submit\">Save</button>\r\n      <button type=\"reset\" value=\"Reset\">Print</button>\r\n</div>\n1\nINCLUDE: \"[your-subject]\"\nINCLUDE: <wordpress@include.xyz>\nbomoxuxul@parcel4.net\nFrom: [your-name] <[your-email]>\r\nSubject: [your-subject]\r\n\r\nMessage Body:\r\n[your-message]\r\n\r\n-- \r\nThis e-mail was sent from a contact form on INCLUDE: (http://include.xyz)\n\n\n\n\n\nINCLUDE: \"[your-subject]\"\nINCLUDE: <wordpress@include.xyz>\n[your-email]\nMessage Body:\r\n[your-message]\r\n\r\n-- \r\nThis e-mail was sent from a contact form on INCLUDE: (http://include.xyz)\nReply-To: bomoxuxul@parcel4.net\n\n\n\nThank you for your message. It has been sent.\nThere was an error trying to send your message. Please try again later.\nOne or more fields have an error. Please check and try again.\nThere was an error trying to send your message. Please try again later.\nYou must accept the terms and conditions before sending your message.\nThe field is required.\nThe field is too long.\nThe field is too short.\nThe date format is incorrect.\nThe date is before the earliest one allowed.\nThe date is after the latest one allowed.\nThere was an unknown error uploading the file.\nYou are not allowed to upload files of this type.\nThe f