ultural values and expectations of the different groups and communities being served?</li>\n 	<li>how can the programme be most effectively structured and managed?</li>\n</ul>','Introduction','','inherit','closed','closed','','235-autosave-v1','','','2019-08-08 11:12:08','2019-08-08 11:12:08','',235,'http://include.xyz/2019/05/30/235-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(289,1,'2019-05-30 05:05:15','2019-05-30 05:05:15','<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-237\" src=\"http://include.xyz/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/management_new_0-300x242.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"242\" />\n<div id=\"node-book-full-group-calout-inner\" class=\"callout-inner col-xs-12 col-sm-9 col-md-9 col-lg-9\">\n<div class=\"field field-name-field-callout-text field-type-text-long field-label-hidden\">\n<div class=\"field-items\">\n<div class=\"field-item even\">\n\nA well-managed CBR activity:\n<ul>\n 	<li>implements the CBR components that best match the needs, priorities and resources of the community;</li>\n 	<li>is inclusive of all key community stakeholders, especially people with disabilities, their family members and organizations that represent them; and</li>\n 	<li>ensures equal treatment by implementing the rights in the Convention on the Rights of Persons with Disabilities (CRPD).</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div id=\"node-book-full-group-img-container\" class=\"img-container col-xs-12 col-sm-3 col-md-3 col-lg-3\">\n<div class=\"field field-name-field-callout-image field-type-image field-label-hidden\">\n<div class=\"field-items\"></div>\n</div>\n</div>','Preamble','','inherit','closed','closed','','236-autosave-v1','','','2019-05-30 05:05:15','2019-05-30 05:05:15','',236,'http://include.xyz/2019/05/30/236-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(290,1,'2019-05-30 05:38:03','2019-05-30 05:38:03','a:10:{s:4:\"type\";s:4:\"text\";s:12:\"instructions\";s:0:\"\";s:8:\"required\";i:0;s:17:\"conditional_logic\";i:0;s:7:\"wrapper\";a:3:{s:5:\"width\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"class\";s:0:\"\";s:2:\"id\";s:0:\"\";}s:13:\"default_value\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"placeholder\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"prepend\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"append\";s:0:\"\";s:9:\"maxlength\";s:0:\"\";}','Parent Module','parent_module','publish','closed','closed','','field_5cef6c270fd16','','','2019-05-30 05:38:03','2019-05-30 05:38:03','',279,'http://include.xyz/?post_type=acf-field&p=290',4,'acf-field','',0),(293,1,'2019-05-30 05:50:02','2019-05-30 05:50:02','<div class=\"border border-dark \">Before you begin this module, we urge you to take a few moments to reflect on your expectations about this online course, as well as your previous experience (if any) with CBR.\n','Introduction','','inherit','closed','closed','','176-autosave-v1','','','2019-05-30 05:50:02','2019-05-30 05:50:02','',176,'http://include.xyz/2019/05/30/176-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(294,1,'2019-05-30 06:03:59','2019-05-30 06:03:59','<div class=\"page-number\">\r\n 	 Page 1/40\r\n </div>\r\n<p>Welcome to INCLUDE!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The key message is to<strong>promote CBR as a strategy</strong>to:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>realize the rights of people with disabilities at the community level;</li>\r\n 	<li>support people with disabilities and their families in getting out of poverty;</li>\r\n 	<li>support stakeholders so that people with disabilities and their families can satisfy their basic needs, improve their daily lives, and access health, education, livelihood, social and other services;</li>\r\n 	<li>promote the empowerment of people with disabilities and their families in their communities; and</li>\r\n 	<li>support decision-making by people with disabilities on an equal basis with others.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','Key messages','','publish','closed','closed','','key-messages','','','2019-08-09 10:08:21','2019-08-09 10:08:21','',0,'http://include.xyz/?post_type=chapters&#038;p=294',0,'chapters','',0),(295,1,'2019-05-30 06:05:05','2019-05-30 06:05:05','<div class=\"page-number\">\r\n 	 Page 2/40\r\n </div>\r\n<p>This course consists of the following learning modules:</p>\r\n\r\n<strong>Module 1  Introduction</strong>\r\n\r\n<p>The Introduction provides an overview of the concept of disability and its evolution, the Convention on the Rights of Persons with Disabilities (CRPD), the development of CBR leading to the creation of the CBR matrix and the CBR Guidelines.</p>\r\n\r\n<strong>Modules 27</strong>\r\n\r\n<p>These modules begin by examining issues in Management, and then consider in turn each of the five basic components of the CBR Matrix  Health, Education, Livelihood, Social and Empowerment  each of which is broken down into its subcomponents and discussed separately.</p>\r\n\r\n<strong>Module 8</strong>\r\n\r\n<p>This supplementary module covers four additional topics, not previously considered in CBR: mental health, HIV/AIDS, leprosy and humanitarian crises.</p>\r\n\r\n','Course overview','','publish','closed','closed','','course-overview','','','2019-08-09 10:23:58','2019-08-09 10:23:58','',0,'http://include.xyz/?post_type=chapters&#038;p=295',0,'chapters','',0),(296,1,'2019-05-30 06:05:48','2019-05-30 06:05:48','<div class=\"page-number\">\r\n 	 Page 3/40\r\n </div>\r\n<p>The objectives of this Introduction module are to:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>provide a brief overview of CBR, its history and the CBR Guidelines</li>\r\n 	<li>introduce the evolving concept of disability</li>\r\n 	<li>introduce the Convention on the Rights of Persons with Disabilities</li>\r\n 	<li>look at development and inclusive development</li>\r\n 	<li>look at CBR as a strategy for disability-inclusive development, now and in the future.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','Objectives of the Introduction module','','publish','closed','closed','','objectives-of-the-introduction-module','','','2019-08-09 10:24:33','2019-08-09 10:24:33','',0,'http://include.xyz/?post_type=chapters&#038;p=296',0,'chapters','',0),(297,1,'2019-05-30 06:28:57','2019-05-30 06:28:57','\n<>The objectives of this Introduction module are to:\n<ul>\n 	<li>provide a brief overview of CBR, its history and the CBR Guidelines</li>\n 	<li>introduce the evolving concept of disability</li>\n 	<li>introduce the Convention on the Rights of Persons with Disabilities</li>\n 	<li>look at development and inclusive development</li>\n 	<li>look at CBR as a strategy for disability-inclusive development, now and in the future.</li>\n</ul>\n','Objectives of the Introduction module','','inherit','closed','closed','','296-autosave-v1','','','2019-05-30 06:28:57','2019-05-30 06:28:57','',296,'http://include.xyz/2019/05/30/296-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(298,1,'2019-05-30 06:31:53','2019-05-30 06:31:53','\nThis course consists of the following learning modules:\n\n<strong>Module 1  Introduction</strong>\n\nThe Introduction provides an overview of the concept of disability and its evolution, the Convention on the Rights of Persons with Disabilities (CRPD), the development of CBR leading to the creation of the CBR matrix and the CBR Guidelines.</p>\n\n<strong>Modules 27</strong>\n\n<p>These modules begin by examining issues in Management, and then consider in turn each of the five basic components of the CBR Matrix  Health, Education, Livelihood, Social and Empowerment  each of which is broken down into its subcomponents and discussed separately.</p>\n\n<strong>Module 8</strong>\n\n<p>This supplementary module covers four additional topics, not previously considered in CBR: mental health, HIV/AIDS, leprosy and humanitarian crises.</p>\n\n','Course overview','','inherit','closed','closed','','295-autosave-v1','','','2019-05-30 06:31:53','2019-05-30 06:31:53','',295,'http://include.xyz/2019/05/30/295-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(299,1,'2019-05-30 06:33:36','2019-05-30 06:33:36','\n<p>Welcome to INCLUDE!</p>\n\n<p>The key message is to<strong>promote CBR as a strategy</strong>to:</p>\n<ul>\n 	<li>realize the rights of people with disabilities at the community level;</li>\n 	<li>support people with disabilities and their families in getting out of poverty;</li>\n 	<li>support stakeholders so that people with disabilities and their families can satisfy their basic needs, improve their daily lives, and access health, education, livelihood, social and other services;</li>\n 	<li>promote the empowerment of people with disabilities and their families in their communities; and</li>\n 	<li>support decision-making by people with disabilities on an equal basis with others.</li>\n</ul>\n','Key messages','','inherit','closed','closed','','294-autosave-v1','','','2019-05-30 06:33:36','2019-05-30 06:33:36','',294,'http://include.xyz/2019/05/30/294-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(300,1,'2019-05-30 06:44:45','2019-05-30 06:44:45','<p>\r\nThe material presented in this module is designed to help you adapt your CBR so that it best satisfies the needs, priorities and resources of the communities you serve. Specifically, you will learn how to:</p><ul>\r\n 	<li>select the components and elements of the CBR matrix relevant and appropriate to your situation;</li>\r\n 	<li>employ a participatory style of management to increase the inclusiveness and sustainability of your CBR;</li>\r\n 	<li>use a proven four-stage management cycle to engage people with disabilities, their families and governments and funding bodies actively in the CBR process and effectively respond to the needs of people with disabilities and their families; and</li>\r\n 	<li>build a programme aligned with both the CBR Guidelines and the Convention on the Rights of Persons with Disabilities (CRPD).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','What you will learn in this module','','publish','closed','closed','','what-you-will-learn-in-this-module-2','','','2019-05-30 08:00:21','2019-05-30 08:00:21','',0,'http://include.xyz/?post_type=chapters&#038;p=300',0,'chapters','',0),(301,1,'2019-05-30 08:00:00','2019-05-30 08:00:00','<p>\nThe material presented in this module is designed to help you adapt your CBR so that it best satisfies the needs, priorities and resources of the communities you serve. Specifically, you will learn how to:\n<ul>\n 	<li>select the components and elements of the CBR matrix relevant and appropriate to your situation;</li>\n 	<li>employ a participatory style of management to increase the inclusiveness and sustainability of your CBR;</li>\n 	<li>use a proven four-stage management cycle to engage people with disabilities, their families and governments and funding bodies actively in the CBR process and effectively respond to the needs of people with disabilities and their families; and</li>\n 	<li>build a programme aligned with both the CBR Guidelines and the Convention on the Rights of Persons with Disabilities (CRPD).</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>','What you will learn in this module','','inherit','closed','closed','','300-autosave-v1','','','2019-05-30 08:00:00','2019-05-30 08:00:00','',300,'http://include.xyz/2019/05/30/300-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(302,1,'2019-05-30 08:02:22','2019-05-30 08:02:22','<h3 class=\"page-header\">Desirable outcomes</h3>\n\n<p><strong>People with disabilities</strong>are:</p>\n<ul>\n 	<li>actively and meaningfully involved in the management of CBR.</li>\n</ul>\n<><strong>CBR activities:</strong>\n<ul>\n 	<li>are based on a thorough analysis of the needs of all people with disabilities, including those most at risk of exclusion;</li>\n 	<li>mobilize and coordinate relevant stakeholders;</li>\n 	<li>build a sense of joint ownership among all stakeholders in support of programme sustainability;</li>\n 	<li>effectively contribute at an affordable cost to building inclusive communities and realizing the rights of all community members, including persons with disabilities; and</li>\n 	<li>develop the capacities of CBR staff to ensure continual quality improvement.</li>\n</ul>\nWithin the<strong>community</strong>:\n<ul>\n 	<li>decision-makers will put in place policies that implement the CRPD and budget for the inclusion of people with disabilities; and</li>\n 	<li>service providers will deliver services that are accessible and inclusive.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</section></div>','Desirable outcomes','','inherit','closed','closed','','240-autosave-v1','','','2019-05-30 08:02:22','2019-05-30 08:02:22','',240,'http://include.xyz/2019/05/30/240-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(303,1,'2019-05-30 08:06:01','2019-05-30 08:06:01','<h3 class=\"page-header\">Elements in this module</h3>\n\n<p>The Management module is made up of the following elements.</p>\n\n<em>Use your mouse or keyboard to expand each of the headings below.</em>\n\n\n<div class=\"region region-content\"><section id=\"block-system-main\" class=\"block block-system clearfix\">\n<div id=\"node-802\" class=\"node node-key-concepts clearfix\">\n<div class=\"content\">\n<div id=\"node-key-concepts-full-group-content-wrapper\" class=\"content-wrapper row\">\n<div class=\"field field-name-field-content field-type-text-long field-label-hidden\">\n<div class=\"field-items\">\n<div class=\"field-item even\"></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</section></div>','Elements in this module','','inherit','closed','closed','','242-autosave-v1','','','2019-05-30 08:06:01','2019-05-30 08:06:01','',242,'http://include.xyz/2019/05/30/242-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(304,1,'2019-05-30 08:23:37','2019-05-30 08:23:37','<h3 class=\"page-header\">Management structures</h3>\n\n<p>In this section you will learn about the several ways that CBR can be structured</p>\n\n<div class=\"region region-content\"><section id=\"block-system-main\" class=\"block block-system clearfix\">\n<div id=\"node-801\" class=\"node node-book clearfix\">\n<div class=\"content\">\n<div id=\"node-book-full-group-callout-wrapper\" class=\"callout-wrapper row\">\n<div id=\"node-book-full-group-calout-inner\" class=\"callout-inner col-xs-12 col-sm-9 col-md-9 col-lg-9\">\n<div class=\"field field-name-field-callout-text field-type-text-long field-label-hidden\">\n<h3 class=\"field-item even\"><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-237\" src=\"http://include.xyz/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/management_new_0-300x242.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"242\" /></h3>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</section></div>','Management structures','','inherit','closed','closed','','243-autosave-v1','','','2019-05-30 08:23:37','2019-05-30 08:23:37','',243,'http://include.xyz/2019/05/30/243-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(305,1,'2019-05-30 08:55:38','2019-05-30 08:55:38','Access to education is critical for achievement of every individuals full potential. This module describes strategies CBR programmes can use to move society towards this lofty goal.','Education',' Access to education is critical for achievement of every individuals full potential. This module describes strategies CBR programmes can use to move society towards this lofty goal. ','publish','closed','closed','','education','','','2019-05-30 08:55:38','2019-05-30 08:55:38','',0,'http://include.xyz/?post_type=modules&#038;p=305',0,'modules','',0),(306,1,'2019-05-30 09:07:28','2019-05-30 09:07:28','<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-307\" src=\"http://include.xyz/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/health_new-1-300x242.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"242\" />CBR programmes support the health and well-being of people with disabilities in five key areas covered in this module: health promotion, prevention, medical care, rehabilitation and assistive devices.','Health','CBR programmes support the health and well-being of people with disabilities in five key areas covered in this module: health promotion, prevention, medical care, rehabilitation and assistive devices.','inherit','closed','closed','','179-autosave-v1','','','2019-05-30 09:07:28','2019-05-30 09:07:28','',179,'http://include.xyz/2019/05/30/179-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(307,1,'2019-05-30 09:07:06','2019-05-30 09:07:06','','health_new','','inherit','open','closed','','health_new-2','','','2019-05-30 09:07:06','2019-05-30 09:07:06','',179,'http://include.xyz/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/health_new-1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(308,1,'2019-05-30 09:12:25','2019-05-30 09:12:25','<p>Before you begin viewing the material in this module, we strongly suggest that you take a few moments to reflect on your own thoughts about the role of CBR in health.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Evidence shows that people with disabilities often experience poorer levels of health than the general population. They also face a number of different challenges to the enjoyment of their right to health.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The right to health is not only about access to health services; it is also about access to the underlying determinants of health, such as safe drinking water, adequate sanitation and housing.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The right to health also brings freedoms and entitlements.</p>\r\n<div class=\"row\">\r\n<div class=\"col-md-6\">\r\n<div class=\"border p-3 health-box\">\r\n<strong>Freedoms</strong>include the rights to be free from:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>non-consensual medical treatments (e.g. experiments and research)</li>\r\n 	<li>torture and other cruel, inhuman or degrading treatment</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"col-md-6\">\r\n<div class=\"border p-3 health-box\">\r\n<strong>Entitlements</strong>include the rights to:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>a system of health protection</li>\r\n 	<li>prevention, treatment and control of diseases</li>\r\n 	<li>access to essential medicines</li>\r\n 	<li>participation in health-related decision-making</li>\r\n</ul></div></div></div>\r\n','Introduction to health','','publish','closed','closed','','introduction-to-health','','','2019-05-30 13:41:00','2019-05-30 13:41:00','',179,'http://include.xyz/?post_type=modules&#038;p=308',0,'modules','',0),(309,1,'2019-05-30 09:35:44','2019-05-30 09:35:44','<p>Before you begin viewing the material in this module, we strongly suggest that you take a few moments to reflect on your own thoughts about the role of CBR in health.</p>\n\n<p>Evidence shows that people with disabilities often experience poorer levels of health than the general population. They also face a number of different challenges to the enjoyment of their right to health.</p>\n\n<p>The right to health is not only about access to health services; it is also about access to the underlying determinants of health, such as safe drinking water, adequate sanitation and housing.</p>\n\n<p>The right to health also brings freedoms and entitlements.</p>\n<div class=\"row\">\n<div class=\"col-md-6\">\n<div class=\"border p-3\">\n<strong>Freedoms</strong>include the rights to be free from:\n<ul>\n 	<li>non-consensual medical treatments (e.g. experiments and research)</li>\n 	<li>torture and other cruel, inhuman or degrading treatment</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"col-md-6\">\n<div class=\"border p-3 health-box\">\n<strong>Entitlements</strong>include the rights to:\n<ul>\n 	<li>a system of health protection</li>\n 	<li>prevention, treatment and control of diseases</li>\n 	<li>access to essential medicines</li>\n 	<li>participation in health-related decision-making</li>\n</ul></div></div></div>\n','Introduction to health','','inherit','closed','closed','','308-autosave-v1','','','2019-05-30 09:35:44','2019-05-30 09:35:44','',308,'http://include.xyz/2019/05/30/308-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(310,1,'2019-05-30 09:41:56','2019-05-30 09:41:56','<p class=\"border\">People with disabilities need to be able to reach their highest attainable standard of health.</p>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-311\" src=\"http://include.xyz/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/health_new_0-300x242.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"242\" />','Preamble','','publish','closed','closed','','preamble','','','2019-05-30 09:42:04','2019-05-30 09:42:04','',179,'http://include.xyz/?post_type=modules&#038;p=310',0,'modules','',0),(311,1,'2019-05-30 09:41:39','2019-05-30 09:41:39','','health_new_0','','inherit','open','closed','','health_new_0','','','2019-05-30 09:41:39','2019-05-30 09:41:39','',310,'http://include.xyz/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/health_new_0.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(312,1,'2019-05-30 09:43:28','2019-05-30 09:43:28','<p>The right to health without discrimination is captured in various international instruments.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><strong>The World Health Organization (WHO) Constitution</strong>states that enjoyment of the highest attainable standard of health is one of the fundamental rights of every human being without distinction of race, religion, political belief, economic or social condition.</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>The United Nations Convention on the Rights of Persons with Disabilities (CRPD)</strong>also addresses the right to health for people with disabilities.\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Article 25 requires States to recognize that persons with disabilities have the right to the enjoyment of the highest attainable standard of health without discrimination on the basis of disability.</li>\r\n 	<li>Together with Articles 20 (personal mobility) and 26 (habilitation and rehabilitation), it also outlines measures States Parties should undertake to ensure that people with disabilities are able to access health services that are gender-sensitive, including health-related rehabilitation.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','Health is a fundamental right','','publish','closed','closed','','health-is-a-fundamental-right','','','2019-05-30 09:52:55','2019-05-30 09:52:55','',310,'http://include.xyz/?post_type=modules&#038;p=312',0,'modules','',0),(313,1,'2019-05-30 09:44:31','2019-05-30 09:44:31','<p>The right to health without discrimination is captured in various international instruments.</p>\n<ul>\n 	<li><strong>The World Health Organization (WHO) Constitution</strong>states that enjoyment of the highest attainable standard of health is one of the fundamental rights of every human being without distinction of race, religion, political belief, economic or social condition.</li>\n 	<li><strong>The United Nations Convention on the Rights of Persons with Disabilities (CRPD)</strong>also addresses the right to health for people with disabilities.\n<ul>\n 	<li>Article 25 requires States to recognize that persons with disabilities have the right to the enjoyment of the highest attainable standard of health without discrimination on the basis of disability.</li>\n 	<li>Together with Articles 20 (personal mobility) and 26 (habilitation and rehabilitation), it also outlines measures States Parties should undertake to ensure that people with disabilities are able to access health services that are gender-sensitive, including health-related rehabilitation.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>','Health is a fundamental right','','inherit','closed','closed','','312-autosave-v1','','','2019-05-30 09:44:31','2019-05-30 09:44:31','',312,'http://include.xyz/2019/05/30/312-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(314,1,'2019-05-30 10:03:51','2019-05-30 10:03:51','Why do you think people with disabilities are often discriminated against in health care?\r\n\r\nEnter your thoughts in the box below. Select Save when you are finished.\r\n<textarea class=\"form-control form-textarea\" id=\"edit-extra-health-reflect1-txt\" name=\"extra_health_reflect1_txt\" cols=\"60\" rows=\"3\" spellcheck=\"false\"></textarea>','Take a moment to reflect','','publish','closed','closed','','take-a-moment-to-reflect','','','2019-05-30 10:05:02','2019-05-30 10:05:02','',310,'http://include.xyz/?post_type=modules&#038;p=314',0,'modules','',0),(315,1,'2019-05-30 10:08:10','2019-05-30 10:08:10','To achieve the goal of helping people with disabilities to reach their highest attainable level of health, CBR works across five key areas:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>health promotion</li>\r\n 	<li>prevention</li>\r\n 	<li>medical care</li>\r\n 	<li>rehabilitation, and</li>\r\n 	<li>assistive devices</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nAs the view of disability has altered from a purely medical approach to one that recognizes the importance of social and environmental influences on disability, CBR has become a multisectoral approach that works across many sectors, such as education and livelihood.\r\n\r\nBecause health is such a large topic, this module will focus primarily on CBR activities that take place within the health sector.','CBR and health','','publish','closed','closed','','cbr-and-health','','','2019-05-30 10:08:10','2019-05-30 10:08:10','',310,'http://include.xyz/?post_type=modules&#038;p=315',0,'modules','',0),(316,1,'2019-05-30 10:14:12','2019-05-30 10:14:12','<div class=\"border border-dark\">The role of CBR is to work with the health sector to ensure that the needs of people with disabilities and their families are addressed in all aspects of health, including health promotion, prevention, medical care, rehabilitation and assistive devices.</div>\r\n1. Which of these role(s) does your organization already perform? Please record your thoughts in the box below.\r\n<textarea id=\"edit-extra-health-role-cbr1-txt1\" class=\"form-control form-textarea\" spellcheck=\"false\" cols=\"60\" name=\"extra_health_role_cbr1_txt1\" rows=\"3\"></textarea>\r\n\r\n2. In which role(s) would you like to increase your capacity in order to better respond to the needs of the people with disabilities? Enter your thoughts in the box below; and select Save when you are finished.\r\n<textarea id=\"edit-extra-health-role-cbr1-txt1\" class=\"form-control form-textarea\" spellcheck=\"false\" cols=\"60\" name=\"extra_health_role_cbr1_txt1\" rows=\"3\"></textarea>','Role of CBR','','publish','closed','closed','','role-of-cbr','','','2019-05-30 10:15:14','2019-05-30 10:15:14','',310,'http://include.xyz/?post_type=modules&#038;p=316',0,'modules','',0),(317,1,'2019-05-30 10:16:40','2019-05-30 10:16:40','<div id=\"node-book-full-group-content-wrapper\" class=\"content-wrapper row\">\r\n<div class=\"field field-name-field-content field-type-text-long field-label-hidden\">\r\n<div class=\"field-items\">\r\n<div class=\"field-item even\">\r\n\r\n<strong>People with disabilities</strong>are able to:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>participate actively in family and community life.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>People with disabilities and their families</strong>are able to:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>demonstrate improved knowledge about their health, and about the importance of giving free and informed consent;</li>\r\n 	<li>actively participate in achieving good health;</li>\r\n 	<li>access affordable rehabilitation and health-care services (including sexual and reproductive health) close to home.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThe<strong>health sector</strong>:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>is aware that people with disabilities can achieve good health</li>\r\n 	<li>does not discriminate on the basis of disability or other factors, such as gender</li>\r\n 	<li>always provides treatment and care on the basis of free and informed consent.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>All development sectors</strong>, including education, livelihood and social sectors, collaborate to achieve good health for persons with disabilities.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>','Desirable outcomes','','publish','closed','closed','','desirable-outcomes','','','2019-05-30 10:16:40','2019-05-30 10:16:40','',310,'http://include.xyz/?post_type=modules&#038;p=317',0,'modules','',0),(318,1,'2019-05-30 10:28:25','2019-05-30 10:28:25','Here are some of the most important ideas you need to understand in order to ensure that people with disabilities and their families are able to obtain the health services that they need.\r\n\r\n<em>Use your mouse or keyboard to expand each of the headings below.</em>\r\n<div class=\"accordion active\">\r\n<div class=\"accordion-title accordian-keyconcept\">What is health?</div>\r\n<div class=\"accordion-desc\" style=\"display: block;\">\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Health has been defined by WHO as a state of complete physical, mental and social well-being and not merely the absence of disease or infirmity.</li>\r\n 	<li>Health is a valuable resource that enables people to lead individually, socially and economically productive lives, providing them with the capacity to work, learn and fully engage in family and community life.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"accordion active\">\r\n<div class=\"accordion-title accordian-keyconcept\">Determinants of health</div>\r\n<div class=\"accordion-desc\" style=\"display: block;\">\r\n\r\nA persons health status is influenced by a wide range of personal, economic, social and environmental factors. These factors are commonly referred to as determinants of health and include:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><strong>genetics</strong> inherited characteristics play a part in determining lifespan, healthiness and the likelihood of developing certain diseases and conditions;</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>individual behaviours and lifestyle</strong> diet, activity, smoking, drinking and how we deal with lifes stresses all affect health;</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>income and social status</strong> the greater the gap between rich and poor people, the greater the differences in health;</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>employment and working conditions</strong> people in employment tend to be healthier, particularly those who have more control over their working conditions;</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>education</strong> low education levels tend to be linked with poorer health;</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>social support networks</strong> greater support from families, friends and communities is linked with better health;</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>culture</strong> customs and traditions and the beliefs of the family and community all affect health;</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>gender</strong> men and women suffer from different types of diseases at different ages;</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>physical environment</strong> safe water and clean air, healthy workplaces, safe houses, communities and roads all contribute to good health;</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>health services</strong> access to and use of services influence health.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"accordion active\">\r\n<div class=\"accordion-title accordian-keyconcept\">Social determinants of health</div>\r\n<div class=\"accordion-desc\" style=\"display: block;\">\r\n\r\nThe social determinants of health are the social conditions in which people are born, grow, live, work and age. These circumstances are shaped by the distribution of income, power and resources at global, national and local levels.\r\n\r\nThe social determinants of health are responsible for health inequities, which are not merely differences in health, but differences in access to the resources needed for better health. To address health inequities, WHO Member States adopted the Rio Political Declaration on Social Determinants of Health at the World Conference on Social Determinants of Health in Rio de Janeiro, Brazil in October 2011, calling for action in five areas:\r\n\r\nadopt improved governance for health and development\r\n\r\npromote participation in policy-making and implementation\r\n\r\nfurther reorient the health sector towards promoting health and reducing health inequities\r\n\r\nstrengthen global governance and collaboration\r\n\r\nmonitor progress and increase accountability.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"accordion active\">\r\n<div class=\"accordion-title accordian-keyconcept\">Disability and health</div>\r\n<div class=\"accordion-desc\" style=\"display: block;\">\r\n\r\nHealth for All was a global health objective set by WHO during theInternational Conference on Primary Health Care (Alma-Ata, USSR,<em></em>612 September 1978). Today, communities globally have yet to achieve this objective.\r\n\r\nTo ensure that people with disabilities achieve good levels of health, it is important to remember that:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>people with disabilities need health services for general health-care needs, such as health promotion and prevention services, and medical care like the rest of the population, including different needs in different phases of life;</li>\r\n 	<li>while not all people with disabilities have further health problems related to their impairments, many will require specific health-care services, including rehabilitation, on a regular or occasional basis and for limitedperiods or long-term also, people with impairments tend to be more vulnerable to other health problems, including injuries.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"accordion active\">\r\n<div class=\"accordion-title accordian-keyconcept\">Health care</div>\r\n<div class=\"accordion-desc\" style=\"display: block;\">\r\n<div class=\"accordion active\">\r\n<div class=\"accordion-title accordian-keyconcept\">Health-care provision <span class=\"float-right\"></span></div>\r\n<div class=\"accordion-desc\" style=\"display: block;\">\r\n\r\nHealth care is provided by the health system, which comprises all those organizations, institutions, resources and people whose primary purpose is to promote, restore or maintain health and enhance functioning. While the ultimate responsibility for the health system lies with the government, most health care is provided by a combination of public, private, traditional and informal sectors.\r\n\r\nThe 2008 World Health Report emphasizes the essential role of primary health care in achieving health for every person. Primary health care is essential health care and should be made universally accessible to individuals and families at a cost they can afford. It is the first level of contact with the national health system for individuals, families and communities, and should bring health care as close as possible to where people live and work.\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"accordion active\">\r\n<div class=\"accordion-title accordian-keyconcept\">Barriers to health-care services for people with disabilities</div>\r\n<div class=\"accordion-desc\" style=\"display: block;\">\r\n<p>The poor health that people with disabilities may experience may, or may not, be a direct result of having a disability; it can also be linked to difficulties in accessing health services and programmes.</p>\r\n<p>\r\nThe barriers to health-care services that people with disabilities and their family members may face include:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><strong>absent or inappropriate policies and legislation</strong> legislation and policies guaranteeing the rights of people with disabilities to equal access to health services may not exist and, where they do exist, they may not be implemented or enforced;</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>economic barriers</strong> health interventions such as assessments, treatments and medications often require out-of-pocket payments, presenting difficulties for people with disabilities and their families, who are likely to have limited income for health care (see<a href=\"http://include.edc.org/introduction\">Introduction: Poverty and disability</a>);</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>physical and geographical barriers</strong> common physical and geographical barriers include lack of accessible transport, inaccessible buildings and medical equipment and limited health-care resources in rural areas;</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>communication and information barriers</strong> communicating with health workers may be difficult, for example a deaf person may find it difficult to communicate his or her symptoms to a doctor, or health information may not be available in accessible formats, such as picture formats for people with intellectual impairments;</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>poor attitudes and lack of knowledge of health workers about people with disabilities</strong> health personnel may be prejudiced or insensitive, lack awareness about disability and lack the knowledge, understanding and skills to manage health issues for people with disabilities;</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>poor knowledge and attitudes of people with disabilities about general health care and services</strong> people with disabilities may have limited knowledge about their rights and health issues and about what health services are available.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<article class=\"poll-embed node-963 node node-advpoll clearfix\" tabindex=\"-1\">\r\n<h4 class=\"element-invisible\"></h4>\r\n\r\n<strong>Poll question:</strong>Which one of the barriers mentioned above do you believe is most significant in your community?\r\n\r\n</article>Some people with disabilities may be more vulnerable to discrimination and exclusion than others. They may suffer double or multiple disadvantages, due to the type of disability they have, their age, gender or social status.\r\n\r\nCBR should be particularly mindful of the following groups:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>women</li>\r\n 	<li>children and older people with disabilities</li>\r\n 	<li>people with multiple impairments</li>\r\n 	<li>people who have intellectual impairments</li>\r\n 	<li>people with<a href=\"http://include.edc.org/supplementary/671/hiv-and-aids\">HIV/AIDS</a></li>\r\n 	<li>people who have<a href=\"http://include.edc.org/supplementary/671/mental-health\">mental health problems</a>,<a href=\"http://include.edc.org/supplementary/671/leprosy\">leprosy</a>, or albinism.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"accordion active\">\r\n<div class=\"accordion-title accordian-keyconcept\">Inclusive health</div>\r\n<div class=\"accordion-desc\" style=\"display: block;\">\r\n<p>Inclusive education is increasingly being implemented in education systems throughout the world. It refers to education that welcomes all people, including those with disabilities, to participate fully in regular schools or centres of learning.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Similarly, the concept of inclusive health is now being promoted by CBR to ensure that health systems recognize and accommodate the needs of people with disabilities in their policies, planning and service delivery. It builds on the Health for All concept of primary health care, which states that health care should be  accessible to individuals and families in the community through their full participation and at a cost that the community and the country can afford.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Inclusive health means that all individuals can access health care irrespective of impairment, gender, age, colour, race, religion and socioeconomic status. To ensure this, health-care service providers need to have positive attitudes towards disability and people with disabilities and have the appropriate skills, such as communication skills to accommodate the needs of people with different impairments.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"accordion active\">\r\n<div class=\"accordion-title  accordian-keyconcept\">CBR and the health sector</div>\r\n<div class=\"accordion-desc\" style=\"display: block;\">\r\n<p>CBR can facilitate access to health care for people with disabilities by working with primary health care in the local community, providing the much-needed link between people with disabilities and the health-care system.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In many countries, including Argentina, Indonesia, Mongolia and Viet Nam, CBR activities are directly linked with the health-care system. They are managed by the ministry of health and implemented through primary health care structures.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In other countries, CBR is managed by nongovernmental organizations or other government ministries such as social welfare. In these situations, close contact must be maintained with primary health care to ensure that people with disabilities can access health care and appropriate rehabilitation services as early as possible.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n','Key concepts','','publish','closed','closed','','key-concepts','','','2019-05-30 13:08:09','2019-05-30 13:08:09','',0,'http://include.xyz/?post_type=modules&#038;p=318',0,'modules','',0),(319,1,'2019-05-30 13:04:38','2019-05-30 13:04:38','Here are some of the most important ideas you need to understand in order to ensure that people with disabilities and their families are able to obtain the health services that they need.\n\n<em>Use your mouse or keyboard to expand each of the headings below.</em>\n<div class=\"accordion active\">\n<div class=\"accordion-title accordian-keyconcept\">What is health?</div>\n<div class=\"accordion-desc\" style=\"display: block;\">\n<ul>\n 	<li>Health has been defined by WHO as a state of complete physical, mental and social well-being and not merely the absence of disease or infirmity.</li>\n 	<li>Health is a valuable resource that enables people to lead individually, socially and economically productive lives, providing them with the capacity to work, learn and fully engage in family and community life.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"accordion active\">\n<div class=\"accordion-title accordian-keyconcept\">Determinants of health</div>\n<div class=\"accordion-desc\" style=\"display: block;\">\n\nA persons health status is influenced by a wide range of personal, economic, social and environmental factors. These factors are commonly referred to as determinants of health and include:\n<ul>\n 	<li><strong>genetics</strong> inherited characteristics play a part in determining lifespan, healthiness and the likelihood of developing certain diseases and conditions;</li>\n 	<li><strong>individual behaviours and lifestyle</strong> diet, activity, smoking, drinking and how we deal with lifes stresses all affect health;</li>\n 	<li><strong>income and social status</strong> the greater the gap between rich and poor people, the greater the differences in health;</li>\n 	<li><strong>employment and working conditions</strong> people in employment tend to be healthier, particularly those who have more control over their working conditions;</li>\n 	<li><strong>education</strong> low education levels tend to be linked with poorer health;</li>\n 	<li><strong>social support networks</strong> greater support from families, friends and communities is linked with better health;</li>\n 	<li><strong>culture</strong> customs and traditions and the beliefs of the family and community all affect health;</li>\n 	<li><strong>gender</strong> men and women suffer from different types of diseases at different ages;</li>\n 	<li><strong>physical environment</strong> safe water and clean air, healthy workplaces, safe houses, communities and roads all contribute to good health;</li>\n 	<li><strong>health services</strong> access to and use of services influence health.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"accordion active\">\n<div class=\"accordion-title accordian-keyconcept\">Social determinants of health</div>\n<div class=\"accordion-desc\" style=\"display: block;\">\n\nThe social determinants of health are the social conditions in which people are born, grow, live, work and age. These circumstances are shaped by the distribution of income, power and resources at global, national and local levels.\n\nThe social determinants of health are responsible for health inequities, which are not merely differences in health, but differences in access to the resources needed for better health. To address health inequities, WHO Member States adopted the Rio Political Declaration on Social Determinants of Health at the World Conference on Social Determinants of Health in Rio de Janeiro, Brazil in October 2011, calling for action in five areas:\n\nadopt improved governance for health and development\n\npromote participation in policy-making and implementation\n\nfurther reorient the health sector towards promoting health and reducing health inequities\n\nstrengthen global governance and collaboration\n\nmonitor progress and increase accountability.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<div class=\"accordion active\">\n<div class=\"accordion-title accordian-keyconcept\">Disability and health</div>\n<div class=\"accordion-desc\" style=\"display: block;\">\n\nHealth for All was a global health objective set by WHO during theInternational Conference on Primary Health Care (Alma-Ata, USSR,<em></em>612 September 1978). Today, communities globally have yet to achieve this objective.\n\nTo ensure that people with disabilities achieve good levels of health, it is important to remember that:\n<ul>\n 	<li>people with disabilities need health services for general health-care needs, such as health promotion and prevention services, and medical care like the rest of the population, including different needs in different phases of life;</li>\n 	<li>while not all people with disabilities have further health problems related to their impairments, many will require specific health-care services, including rehabilitation, on a regular or occasional basis and for limitedperiods or long-term also, people with impairments tend to be more vulnerable to other health problems, including injuries.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"accordion active\">\n<div class=\"accordion-title accordian-keyconcept\">Health care</div>\n<div class=\"accordion-desc\" style=\"display: block;\">\n<div class=\"accordion active\">\n<div class=\"accordion-title accordian-keyconcept\">Health-care provision <span class=\"float-right\"></span></div>\n<div class=\"accordion-desc\" style=\"display: block;\">\n\nHealth care is provided by the health system, which comprises all those organizations, institutions, resources and people whose primary purpose is to promote, restore or maintain health and enhance functioning. While the ultimate responsibility for the health system lies with the government, most health care is provided by a combination of public, private, traditional and informal sectors.\n\nThe 2008 World Health Report emphasizes the essential role of primary health care in achieving health for every person. Primary health care is essential health care and should be made universally accessible to individuals and families at a cost they can afford. It is the first level of contact with the national health system for individuals, families and communities, and should bring health care as close as possible to where people live and work.\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<div class=\"accordion active\">\n<div class=\"accordion-title accordian-keyconcept\">Barriers to health-care services for people with disabilities <span class=\"float-right\"></span></div>\n<div class=\"accordion-desc\" style=\"display: block;\">\n<p>The poor health that people with disabilities may experience may, or may not, be a direct result of having a disability; it can also be linked to difficulties in accessing health services and programmes.</p>\n<p>\nThe barriers to health-care services that people with disabilities and their family members may face include:</p>\n<ul>\n 	<li><strong>absent or inappropriate policies and legislation</strong> legislation and policies guaranteeing the rights of people with disabilities to equal access to health services may not exist and, where they do exist, they may not be implemented or enforced;</li>\n 	<li><strong>economic barriers</strong> health interventions such as assessments, treatments and medications often require out-of-pocket payments, presenting difficulties for people with disabilities and their families, who are likely to have limited income for health care (see<a href=\"http://include.edc.org/introduction\">Introduction: Poverty and disability</a>);</li>\n 	<li><strong>physical and geographical barriers</strong> common physical and geographical barriers include lack of accessible transport, inaccessible buildings and medical equipment and limited health-care resources in rural areas;</li>\n 	<li><strong>communication and information barriers</strong> communicating with health workers may be difficult, for example a deaf person may find it difficult to communicate his or her symptoms to a doctor, or health information may not be available in accessible formats, such as picture formats for people with intellectual impairments;</li>\n 	<li><strong>poor attitudes and lack of knowledge of health workers about people with disabilities</strong> health personnel may be prejudiced or insensitive, lack awareness about disability and lack the knowledge, understanding and skills to manage health issues for people with disabilities;</li>\n 	<li><strong>poor knowledge and attitudes of people with disabilities about general health care and services</strong> people with disabilities may have limited knowledge about their rights and health issues and about what health services are available.</li>\n</ul>\n<article class=\"poll-embed node-963 node node-advpoll clearfix\" tabindex=\"-1\">\n<h4 class=\"element-invisible\"></h4>\n\n<strong>Poll question:</strong>Which one of the barriers mentioned above do you believe is most significant in your community?\n\n</article>Some people with disabilities may be more vulnerable to discrimination and exclusion than others. They may suffer double or multiple disadvantages, due to the type of disability they have, their age, gender or social status.\n\nCBR should be particularly mindful of the following groups:\n<ul>\n 	<li>women</li>\n 	<li>children and older people with disabilities</li>\n 	<li>people with multiple impairments</li>\n 	<li>people who have intellectual impairments</li>\n 	<li>people with<a href=\"http://include.edc.org/supplementary/671/hiv-and-aids\">HIV/AIDS</a></li>\n 	<li>people who have<a href=\"http://include.edc.org/supplementary/671/mental-health\">mental health problems</a>,<a href=\"http://include.edc.org/supplementary/671/leprosy\">leprosy</a>, or albinism.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n\n\n<div class=\"accordion active\">\n<div class=\"accordion-title accordian-keyconcept\">Inclusive health <span class=\"float-right\"></span></div>\n<div class=\"accordion-desc\" style=\"display: block;\">\n<p>Inclusive education is increasingly being implemented in education systems throughout the world. It refers to education that welcomes all people, including those with disabilities, to participate fully in regular schools or centres of learning.</p>\n\n<p>Similarly, the concept of inclusive health is now being promoted by CBR to ensure that health systems recognize and accommodate the needs of people with disabilities in their policies, planning and service delivery. It builds on the Health for All concept of primary health care, which states that health care should be  accessible to individuals and families in the community through their full participation and at a cost that the community and the country can afford.</p>\n\n<p>Inclusive health means that all individuals can access health care irrespective of impairment, gender, age, colour, race, religion and socioeconomic status. To ensure this, health-care service providers need to have positive attitudes towards disability and people with disabilities and have the appropriate skills, such as communication skills to accommodate the needs of people with different impairments.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n<div class=\"accordion active\">\n<div class=\"accordion-title  accordian-keyconcept\">CBR and the health sector <span class=\"float-right\"></span></div>\n<div class=\"accordion-desc\" style=\"display: block;\">\n<p>CBR can facilitate access to health care for people with disabilities by working with primary health care in the local community, providing the much-needed link between people with disabilities and the health-care system.</p>\n\n<p>In many countries, including Argentina, Indonesia, Mongolia and Viet Nam, CBR activities are directly linked with the health-care system. They are managed by the ministry of health and implemented through primary health care structures.</p>\n\n<p>In other countries, CBR is managed by nongovernmental organizations or other government ministries such as social welfare. In these situations, close contact must be maintained with primary health care to ensure that people with disabilities can access health care and appropriate rehabilitation services as early as possible.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n','Key concepts','','inherit','closed','closed','','318-autosave-v1','','','2019-05-30 13:04:38','2019-05-30 13:04:38','',318,'http://include.xyz/2019/05/30/318-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(320,1,'2019-05-30 13:49:58','2019-05-30 13:49:58','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>To view or modify an activity in your action plan, use your mouse or keyboard to expand the module heading that contains the activity you want. Then select the activity name from the list that appears on the left-hand side of the screen.</em>[contact-form-7 id=\"110\" title=\"Create supportive environments\"]<br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','My action plan','','inherit','closed','closed','','42-revision-v1','','','2019-05-30 13:49:58','2019-05-30 13:49:58','',42,'http://include.xyz/2019/05/30/42-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(321,1,'2019-05-31 08:58:25','2019-05-31 08:58:25','<div class=\"intro\"> \r\n<p><h5>Support and involve families</h5></p>\r\n<p>CBR personnel can have a major role in supporting and involving families in the process of enabling the local school to be inclusive. Teachers often need to learn that parents are partners in education.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Complete the following form to identify the support strategies you believe will work best in your situation. Select Save when you are finished.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>There are many ways that your organisation can support and involve families in the process of enabling the local school to be inclusive. You will need to work with both parents and teachers to help them each understand that they are partnering together in education for the childrens sake. Use this list of suggested activities below as a starting point to think of more ideas.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTable\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-838 id:cf-321-1 class:cf-321-1 \"Listen and talk to family members about:\"]<ul>\r\n<li>The child with disabilities\' strengths and challenges</li>\r\n<li>The support needed by the child and other family members</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">Use this table as a template for talking with the parents of the children with disabilities.\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableHead p-2 vertical\"><strong>Strengths</strong></div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableHead p-2 vertical\"><strong>Needs (of child)</strong></div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableHead p-2 vertical\"><strong>Challenges</strong></div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableHead p-2 vertical\"><strong>Needs (of family)</strong></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[textarea textarea-187 id:textarea1 class:textarea cols:10 rows:1]</div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[textarea textarea-187 id:textarea1 class:textarea cols:10 rows:1]</div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[textarea textarea-187 id:textarea1 class:textarea cols:10 rows:1]</div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[textarea textarea-187 id:textarea1 class:textarea cols:10 rows:1]</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTable\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-430 id:cf-244-1 class:cf-244-1 \"Liaise between home and school, helping teachers and family members to listen to one another\"]</div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\"><div class=\"rTableRow\">&nbsp</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTable\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-430 id:cf-244-1 class:cf-244-1 \"Observe the child with a disability in the home and explore ways in which learning in school can be continued and supported at home\"]</div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\"><div class=\"rTableRow\">&nbsp</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTable\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-430 id:cf-244-1 class:cf-244-1 \"Help ensure that all decisions are in the best interests of the child, and that his or her rights are protected and realized\"]</div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\"><b>Note:</b> Parents may sometimes: \r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Be overprotective</li>\r\n<li>Have a limited belief in their childs capabilities</li>\r\n<li>Want to prioritize the needs of their other children</li>\r\n</ul><p>Each of these may require a different approach. First identify what, if any, kinds of beliefs already exist, and work with parents to overcome incorrect assumptions and misguided attitudes\r\n</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTable\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-430 id:cf-244-1 class:cf-244-1 \"Promote inclusion with the support of parents\"]</div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\"><b>Note:</b><p> Parents can play a major role  there are many examples where parents have joined together and changed a local schools attitudes and practices so their children are included.</p> \r\n<p>Identify parents in your community who could serve as champions for inclusion:</p>\r\n[textarea textarea-581 id:cf-321-1 class:cf-321-1 cols:60 rows:6]</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTable\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-430 id:cf-244-1 class:cf-244-1 \"Work with parents of children without disabilities to encourage their support for inclusion\"]</div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\"><b>Note:</b> Remember that parents will have different opinions about inclusive education. Some will support the decision to include children with disabilities, while others may feel that their children will be disadvantaged. Work with all parents while being sensitive to these different opinions.</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>Consider this scenario. You have been approached by the parent of a child with no arms who is being refused entry into one of the local primary schools in your community.</p>\r\n<p>What activities could you take with the family of the child to support them and address this issue?</p>\r\n[textarea textarea-944 id:cf-321-1 class:cf-321-1 cols:120 rows:6]\n1\nINCLUDE: \"[your-subject]\"\nINCLUDE: <wordpress@include.xyz>\nbomoxuxul@parcel4.net\nFrom: [your-name] <[your-email]>\r\nSubject: [your-subject]\r\n\r\nMessage Body:\r\n[your-message]\r\n\r\n-- \r\nThis e-mail was sent from a contact form on INCLUDE: (http://include.xyz)\n\n\n\n\n\nINCLUDE: \"[your-subject]\"\nINCLUDE: <wordpress@include.xyz>\n[your-email]\nMessage Body:\r\n[your-message]\r\n\r\n-- \r\nThis e-mail was sent from a contact form on INCLUDE: (http://include.xyz)\nReply-To: bomoxuxul@parcel4.net\n\n\n\nThank you for your message. It has been sent.\nThere was an error trying to send your message. Please try again later.\nOne or more fields have an error. Please check and try again.\nThere was an error trying to send your message. Please try again later.\nYou must accept the terms and conditions before sending your message.\nThe field is required.\nThe field is too long.\nThe field is too short.\nThe date format is incorrect.\nThe date is before the earliest one allowed.\nThe date is after the latest one allowed.\nThere was an unknown error uploading the file.\nYou are not allowed to upload files of this type.\nThe file is too big.\nThere was an error uploading the file.\nThe number format is invalid.\nThe number is smaller than the minimum allowed.\nThe number is larger than the maximum allowed.\nThe answer to the quiz is incorrect.\nYour entered code is incorrect.\nThe e-mail address entered is invalid.\nThe URL is invalid.\nThe telephone number is invalid.','Support and involve families','','publish','closed','closed','','support-and-involve-families-2','','','2019-07-04 13:22:46','2019-07-04 13:22:46','',0,'http://include.xyz/?post_type=wpcf7_contact_form&#038;p=321',0,'wpcf7_contact_form','',0),(323,1,'2019-05-31 08:58:47','2019-05-31 08:58:47','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>To view or modify an activity in your action plan, use your mouse or keyboard to expand the module heading that contains the activity you want. Then select the activity name from the list that appears on the left-hand side of the screen.</em>[contact-form-7 id=\"321\" title=\"Support and involve families\"]<br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','My action plan','','inherit','closed','closed','','42-revision-v1','','','2019-05-31 08:58:47','2019-05-31 08:58:47','',42,'http://include.xyz/2019/05/31/42-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(326,1,'2019-06-03 06:05:35','2019-06-03 06:05:35','<div class=\"intro\"> \r\n<h5><b>Lobby and advocate for inclusion</b></h5>\r\n<p>For inclusion to take place, the system needs to change, yet CBR cannot transform the education system by themselves. CBR personnel need to identify partners and allies. In partnership with other stakeholders (national and local), CBR can advocate for the provision of preschool facilities. Often service providers are aware that inclusive policies or even laws exist, but are not given the help and budgetary support to implement these. CBR should, wherever possible, lobby for existing facilities to become inclusive rather than for the creation of separate facilities.</p>\r\n<p><em>Complete the following form to identify the support strategies you believe will work best in your situation. Select Save when you are finished.</em></p>\r\n<p>Identify some potential partners and allies that your organisation can work with in order to advocate for further inclusion. Who are potential contacts at these organizations? What is their area of focus and interest? Once you have identified these potential partners, make an effort to connect with them and to understand each other\'s goals, work, and interests. Keep in mind that though there may be some differing interests in the programmes and groups you identify, you can find common ground in order to mutually support the inclusion of children with disabilities in early childhood care.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTable\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableHead p-2 vertical\"><b>Persons or groups</b></div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableHead p-2 vertical\"><b>Area of focus</b></div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableHead p-2 vertical\"><b>Contact information</b></div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2\">[text text-15 id:cf-265-1 class:cf-265-1]</div> \r\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2\">[text text-15 id:cf-265-1 class:cf-265-1]</div> \r\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2\">[text text-15 id:cf-265-1 class:cf-265-1]</div> \r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2\">[text text-15 id:cf-265-1 class:cf-265-1]</div> \r\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2\">[text text-15 id:cf-265-1 class:cf-265-1]</div> \r\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2\">[text text-15 id:cf-265-1 class:cf-265-1]</div> \r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2\">[text text-15 id:cf-265-1 class:cf-265-1]</div> \r\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2\">[text text-15 id:cf-265-1 class:cf-265-1]</div> \r\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2\">[text text-15 id:cf-265-1 class:cf-265-1]</div> \r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<button type=\"submit\" value=\"Submit\">Save</button>\r\n      <button type=\"reset\" value=\"Reset\">Print</button>\r\n</div>\n1\nINCLUDE: \"[your-subject]\"\nINCLUDE: <wordpress@include.xyz>\nbomoxuxul@parcel4.net\nFrom: [your-name] <[your-email]>\r\nSubject: [your-subject]\r\n\r\nMessage Body:\r\n[your-message]\r\n\r\n-- \r\nThis e-mail was sent from a contact form on INCLUDE: (http://include.xyz)\n\n\n\n\n\nINCLUDE: \"[your-subject]\"\nINCLUDE: <wordpress@include.xyz>\n[your-email]\nMessage Body:\r\n[your-messag