div>\n\n \n\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','My action plan','','inherit','closed','closed','','42-revision-v1','','','2019-07-15 09:15:50','2019-07-15 09:15:50','',42,'http://include.xyz/2019/07/15/42-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(559,1,'2019-07-15 09:41:05','2019-07-15 09:41:05','<div class=\"intro\"> \r\n<h4><b>Carry out a basic communication assessment</b></h4>\r\n<p>To identify barriers to communication for people with communication difficulties in the community a first step is to undertake a communication assessment.</p>\r\n<p><em>Please answer the following questions to conduct a basic assessment of the current state of communication. Select <b>Save</b> when you are finished.</em></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTable\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">1. Describe the methods of communication your organization is currently using.\r\n[textarea nam1_r1c1 id:cf-556-2 class:textarea cols:100 rows:3]</div> \r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">2. How well are they being used? (Consider the skills of people both with and without disabilities.)\r\n[textarea nam1_r1c1 id:cf-556-2 class:textarea cols:100 rows:3]</div> \r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">3. Is the communication system understood by everyone?Yes[checkbox checkbox-766 id:check class:checkbox]  No[checkbox checkbox-766 id:check class:checkbox]<br>\r\nIf no, who does not understand the system, and what do they fail to understand? \r\n[textarea nam1_r1c1 id:cf-556-2 class:textarea cols:100 rows:3]</div> \r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\r\n4. Do non-disabled individuals really understand the needs of people with disabilities?Yes[checkbox checkbox-766 id:check class:checkbox]  No[checkbox checkbox-766 id:check class:checkbox]<br>\r\nIf no, what do the non-disabled individuals have difficulty understanding?\r\n[textarea nam1_r1c1 id:cf-556-2 class:textarea cols:100 rows:3]</div> \r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">5. With whom do the people with disabilities that you work with usually communicate?<br>\r\n[textarea nam1_r1c1 id:cf-556-2 class:textarea cols:100 rows:3]</div> \r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">6. Do people with disabilities understand what non-disabled people are attempting to communicate with them?Yes[checkbox checkbox-766 id:check class:checkbox]  No[checkbox checkbox-766 id:check class:checkbox]<br>\r\n	If no, what do the disabled individuals have difficulty understanding?<br>\r\n[textarea nam1_r1c1 id:cf-556-2 class:textarea cols:100 rows:3]</div> \r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">7. Why are the people with disabilities that you work with communicating? (For example, is it to join in, express a practical need or express their feelings?)<br>\r\n[textarea nam1_r1c1 id:cf-556-2 class:textarea cols:100 rows:3]</div> \r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">8. What kinds of opportunities to communicate do people with disabilities have? (Do they have many people to talk to, or are they usually left alone?)<br>\r\n[textarea nam1_r1c1 id:cf-556-2 class:textarea cols:100 rows:3]</div> \r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">9. Are there any other barriers to effective communication?Yes[checkbox checkbox-766 id:check class:checkbox]  No[checkbox checkbox-766 id:check class:checkbox]<br>\r\nIf yes, please describe the barriers.<br>\r\n[textarea nam1_r1c1 id:cf-556-2 class:textarea cols:100 rows:3]</div> \r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">10. Do status, power and role influence communication? (For example, does a woman with disabilities talk in front of her spouse? Is a family embarrassed to let their disabled family member communicate?) Yes[checkbox checkbox-766 id:check class:checkbox]  No[checkbox checkbox-766 id:check class:checkbox]<br>\r\nIf yes, please describe the influence.<br>\r\n[textarea nam1_r1c1 id:cf-556-2 class:textarea cols:100 rows:3]</div> \r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">11. Do status, power and role influence communication within your organization? Yes[checkbox checkbox-766 id:check class:checkbox]  No[checkbox checkbox-766 id:check class:checkbox]<br>\r\nIf yes, please describe the influence.<br>\r\n[textarea nam1_r1c1 id:cf-556-2 class:textarea cols:100 rows:3]</div> \r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">12. Do people with disabilities require support to express their opinion, will or preference? Yes[checkbox checkbox-766 id:check class:checkbox]  No[checkbox checkbox-766 id:check class:checkbox]\r\n	If yes:\r\n	<ul><li>If yes, please describe the influence. Yes[checkbox checkbox-766 id:check class:checkbox]  No[checkbox checkbox-766 id:check class:checkbox] </li>\r\n		<li>Is the support person communicating the best interpretation of the will of the person and not speaking on behalf of the person (determining his/her best interest)? Yes[checkbox checkbox-766 id:check class:checkbox]  No[checkbox checkbox-766 id:check class:checkbox] </li>\r\n		<li>Do people in the community recognize the legitimacy of decisions made with support? Yes[checkbox checkbox-766 id:check class:checkbox]  No[checkbox checkbox-766 id:check class:checkbox]</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br><button type=\"submit\" value=\"Submit\">Save</button>\r\n      <button type=\"reset\" value=\"Reset\">Print</button>\r\n  </div>\n1\nINCLUDE: \"[your-subject]\"\nINCLUDE: <wordpress@include.xyz>\nbomoxuxul@parcel4.net\nFrom: [your-name] <[your-email]>\r\nSubject: [your-subject]\r\n\r\nMessage Body:\r\n[your-message]\r\n\r\n-- \r\nThis e-mail was sent from a contact form on INCLUDE: (http://include.xyz)\n\n\n\n\n\nINCLUDE: \"[your-subject]\"\nINCLUDE: <wordpress@include.xyz>\n[your-email]\nMessage Body:\r\n[your-message]\r\n\r\n-- \r\nThis e-mail was sent from a contact form on INCLUDE: (http://include.xyz)\nReply-To: bomoxuxul@parcel4.net\n\n\n\nThank you for your message. It has been sent.\nThere was an error trying to send your message. Please try again later.\nOne or more fields have an error. Please check an