n\n \n\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','My action plan','','inherit','closed','closed','','42-revision-v1','','','2019-08-05 07:26:32','2019-08-05 07:26:32','',42,'http://include.xyz/2019/08/05/42-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(604,1,'2019-08-05 07:50:18','2019-08-05 07:50:18','<div class=\"intro\"> \r\n<h4><b>Encourage self-help group members to participate in CBR programmes</b></h4>\r\n<p>Self-help group members (from both disability-specific and mainstream groups) have the potential to be important resources for CBR programmes. They therefore need to be well informed about CBR. You can encourage self- help group members to participate more in CBR programmes in various ways.</p>\r\n<p><em>Use the planning tool below to think through how you can support and encourage self-help group members to participate in CBR programmes. Select <b>Save</b> when you are finished.</em></p>\r\n<b>1. Identify possible barriers and potential solutions faced by group members</b>\r\n<p>First, identify what barriers current members of self-help groups may face in participating in CBR, as well as potential solution(s) for overcoming those barriers. One possible response is shown below as an example.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTable\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableHead p-2 vertical w-50\"><strong>Possible barriers</strong></div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableHead p-2 vertical w-50\"><strong>Potential solutions</strong></div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical w-50\"><em>Example:</em> Group member(s) does not understand what CBR is.</div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical w-50\"><em>Example:</em> Spend some time with members of the self-help group to explain CBR and its key points.</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[textarea ideiso_r1c2 id:cf-570-7 class:textarea cols:45 rows:3]</div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[textarea ideiso_r1c2 id:cf-570-7 class:textarea cols:45 rows:3]</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[textarea ideiso_r1c2 id:cf-570-7 class:textarea cols:45 rows:3]</div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[textarea ideiso_r1c2 id:cf-570-7 class:textarea cols:45 rows:3]</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>2. Identify potential ways that self-help groups can take part in CBR</b>\r\n<p>Next, identify some potential ways that self-help groups can participate in CBR. Self-help groups can play an important role in creating awareness about disability and promoting inclusive development. Self-help group members may also be able to volunteer their time and contribute to CBR activities. Disability-specific self-help groups should be particularly encouraged to gradually play a bigger role in CBR programmes. Their participation in the management (e.g. planning, implementing and monitoring) of CBR programmes can make programmes more appropriate, credible and sustainable.</p>\r\n<p>Use this list as a starting point and add more ideas as you get to better understand the self-help group members and their interests, goals, and skills more.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Identify people with disabilities in the community</li>\r\n	<li>Support people with rehabilitation activities, and</li>\r\n	<li>Provide follow-up</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Think about the particular interests, goals, and skills of the group members, as well as the unique services and affordances of your organisation. With these in mind, what are some additional ways that self-help group members might participate with CBR programmes?</p>\r\n[textarea khtu_r1c2 id:cf-572-17 class:textarea cols:100 rows:4]\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br><button type=\"submit\" value=\"Submit\">Save</button>\r\n      <button type=\"reset\" value=\"Reset\">Print</button>\r\n</div>\n1\nINCLUDE: \"[your-subject]\"\nI